INSERT INTO `pages` (`id`, `title`, `pc_id`, `userid`, `content`, `alias`, `posted`) VALUES
(1, 'About Us', 1, 1, '    <em>##title##</em> is not just another gaming web site. We aim to not only bring in Minecraft players, but programmers and developers as well. The web site''s author, Paul, started designing web sites when he was thirteen. It is our goal to inspire other people to follow their own dreams, and to create their own ideas. DreamSpand was founded upon an idea: that everyone has a potential, waiting to be unlocked, and that by combining ideas and creativity from the minds of multiple people, greatness can be achieved. The web site started out as a general gaming web site, and after the course of a year, it rapidly transitioned into a Minecraft web site. It''s a game that keeps on growing, and it''s something that can be added on to. We believe it''s a great place for future game developers to start, and the game has real-life applications as well. The site was built from nothing; it was hand-coded and written by one person, not created by a web developer program. Mike created the original ProBoards forum simply called DreamSpand in 2011, and the idea expanded from there. The name was based off of an earler, ongoing forum that was semi-successful named DreamScape, which was also a gaming forum, but featured other aspects as well. After about a year and a half with little to no improvement or attention at all to the ProBoards forum, Paul''s original web site (The Ultimate Chao Garden) was discontinued by it''s host for funding issues. Rather than getting the site back, Paul forged an idea: since his last web site was built from the ground up (exactly like this one), why not do it again? He proposed the idea to Mike and after a month or so the plan was in motion. This version of the web site was originally released on June 6th, 2012, but its build date began on May 15th, 2012. There have been a lot of bumpy roads for the team, but both still believe in the general idea and goals of DreamSpand. The site is not just about bringing players together - it''s about bringing people together, with common interests and powerful concepts, that maybe they just need a bit of a push or motivation to get them started. The site also represents all of our Minecraft servers, and it is the hub for updates and news regarding them. If anything should ever happen to any of our servers as it has in the past, the players know where to go. We offer mods, plugins, schematics, world saves, servers, and in the very near future, we intend to provide resource packs and skins, as well. DreamSpand is home to player and developer alike, and we think that''s what gives it it''s driving force: the fact that the developers can build upon the ideas of the players, and that the players can directly or indirectly influence the developers. If we happen to start a few friendships and partnerships along the way, then well, that''s another goal achieved. DreamSpand is also unique in that it is a friendly-oriented web site. The staff aren''t cold and strict like a lot of site staff are; they''re warm and inviting, and they are more than willing to help the users and players with absolutely anything. If they need someone to talk to, we offer advice and comfort, not just as a healing force, but as a friend. We think it''s important to connect to our users on a level that brings us together, and unites different types of people with a common interest; we also understand, though, that this is not for everyone, and if the members wish to keep to themselves, we understand. The site was simply started with the idea of bringing together people and helping them cope with difficulties and the world around them, by allowing them into our virtual one, where they can build their own ideas. The first forum that Paul owned was called Chao Talk, and its main goal was to bring together people that had problems and struggles, and group them together to have them help each other in overcoming these issues. It was a very successful forum that lasted for eight years, and its motto was "You''re not just a member - you''re a friend." As the co-owner of DreamSpand Gaming, that''s one of the main things that Paul wishes to bring to the table: the feeling of connectivity and friendliness that''s so uncommon in today''s world. Mike also believes in this idea, and in simply starting friendships. We also believe in the concept of an idea: the fact that everything great starts with something small. DreamSpand Gaming wishes to be that starting place for people, that leverage that so many people are looking for, but rarely ever find. If we can push someone to achieve their goals and dreams, then we''ve succeeded in our mission. We''re not just a gaming web site, nor are we just a Minecraft site - we are a site of ideas, concepts, development, friendship and teamwork, and you never have to worry about the staff, or dealing with problematic users. The staff are very vigilent, and all of us wish to provide that feeling of home. We chose Minecraft not just because of its popularity, but because of the concepts we''ve learned from it: that when you provide a place for someone with nowhere to go, or for someone who''s looking for something, they''ll take shelther there; that if you build it, they will come. ', 'about', '2014-12-08 15:51:51'),
