(217, 'DreamSpand Rules [updated 3/22/13]', 'Hello, {display}, and welcome to DreamSpand Gaming''s forums. We want to ensure that you have the best time here that you can possibly have. This will require user interaction, and as such, we have to place a few regulations to try to keep the peace. Follow our rules and we will love you. Always.\n\n[center][size=5]SITE RULES[/size][/center]\n[section=1. Spamming]We hate the stuff, and we''d imagine you do too. As far as the food goes, well we don''t care either way, have at it. We just don''t want useless junk posted on here, or people coming by with those drive-by trollings. Most of all, we hate robots and can''t stand people that just post things for attention. This goes for comments and messages, too. Although users are able to block you in messages, you don''t need to do it in the first place.\n\nWhenever you start a new thread, the post itself must have at least 10 characters in it. That really isn''t asking too much, I don''t think. The submit button will be greyed out until this prerequisite is met.\n\nDon''t just spam around to get our forum medals, either. That''s an easy way to get token-banned, or to have your account disabled. Just don''t spam us and then we can be friends. Forever.\n[section=2. Flaming]This one should go without saying, but have respect for other people on the forum. DreamSpand is not interested in "wars" or anything of the sort. Healthy debating is one thing, but blatant disrespect will make us and others dislike you very much, very quickly.\n\nInstead of just starting an argument in the public, you can just click on the "Report" link directly below the user''s post. We are a friendly community, let''s keep it that way. Have a little decency, just a little bit, and try not to start any trouble. If trouble has already been started, don''t egg it on.\n[section=3. Advertising]Although we understand the need to get the word of your site out to everyone and everywhere possible, don''t just mooch off of our popularity. The web market is tough enough as it is! Once you''ve reached 100 posts, the "web site" field in your profile will show up and you can put it in there. We also accept it in your signature without any requirements, because trust us, we want to help you! There is even a forum achievement (also known as a site medal) for filling out your web site field. In short, we understand, but don''t take advantage of us, either.\n[section=4. Bumping]"Bumping" a post is updating the topic to be the most recent one on the list. This can be done by it being posted in again. Do not do this until someone else has posted in it. Don''t ask a staff member to do it for you, either. Just wait for someone else to post in it.\n[section=5. Authority]Never question a moderator (or a higher rank) about their decision or what they''ve asked you to do. If they ask you to calm down, cool it. There is a difference between keeping order and having an abuse of power. If you feel that there has been a problem, report them using the link at the bottom of their posts. The administrators will see it shortly thereafter and assess the situation.\n\nYou may not like them, but the mods and staff were picked by the admins and owners for a very good reason, and you better respect them for it. We don''t tolerate disrespect here.\n[section=6. Plagiarism]Not only is this a very idiotic move, it''s also unlawful. We will not tolerate any ounce of this. If you are trying to post something from another site, then paraphrase it and provide a source link to it. Although we would prefer you not steal anything from anywhere at all. But by no means should you take credit for something that isn''t yours, or that you didn''t do. We find these things out.\n[section=7. Begging]Don''t bug us about being staff. Asking us "cud i be staf plz" really doesn''t work. Just a little tip, there. And for the record, neither does "Could I be staff, please?" It''s up to the admins of the site to decide this for themselves, and asking them or anyone else will only make your chances even slimmer. You get to be staff by being a decent, loyal member for a good little while, not by puppy dog eyes and cheap scams.\n[section=8. Necromancy]If a topic is old, as in ridiculously old, don''t try to give it CPR. Trust us, it''s gone and resting peacefully. A couple of months is pushing it, but we won''t get you for that. But bring something back from the stone age, such as 4 months or so, and that''s just ridiculous. Instead of replying to the ancient, rotting topic, make another topic similar to it, and maybe include a link to the old topic in your new one. That way you have a reference to it and can kinda add on to it. \n\nHowever, ONLY post in it if you are ADDING value to it, such as new information or an actual, decent post. Those simple little posts just won''t cut it, so don''t do it.\n[section=9. Multiple Accounts]Having more than one account on the site is prohibited except for high staff and admins. We are the only ones that reserve the right to do this, as it is sometimes required. Though even they have to ask permission, first. If you need to sign your friend up or have a similar situation, don''t do it under the radar. We will find out and punish both accounts. So unless you want both you and your "friend''s" accounts terminated, talk to us about it first, by PM or by posting, doesn''t matter.\n[section=10. Excessive Swearing]We understand that the occasional swear word is gonna peer its head every now and again, and if you drop an F-Nuke, we get it. However, if you''re using it excessively, then we got a problem. Don''t be a sailor-mouth. That''s not who we are and that''s not who we want here.\n[section=10. No One Worded Responses]It just makes you (and us) look lazy. Put some effort into the posts, it will be considered spamming if it''s only a few words. There is a minimum word limit of 10 before you can post. Please adhere to it.\n[section=11. Cross-Posting]Don''t start multiple topics that have the same purpose. This will be counted as spam and treated as such.\n[section=12. Different Opinions]Just because someone has a different opinion than you, doesn''t mean they''re wrong. You will respect everyone else''s opinions and will not flame or disrespect them for it.\n[section=13. Safety Precautions]For your own, personal safety, we ask that you do not release any of your personal information on to the site. This could be dangerous.\n[section=14. Leave It To The Mods]Let the moderators and staff handle the out of control situations. Don''t be a God-Mod or try to step in to solve something that''s none of your business. It doesn''t get you turned into staff, it makes you annoying and it adds on to the problem. If you feel like you''ve been wronged, please use the Report This Post link found at the bottom right-hand corner of every post. Staff will be notified about it immediately.\n[section=15. Commercial Advertising]DreamSpand Gaming is not interested in supporting or endorsing any form of product unless otherwise stated by both of the head admins (my buddy Mike and I). This will be counted as spam and you will be permanently banned from the site.\n\n[hr]\nThank you very, very much for reading the rules. That in itself means a lot to us. We''re not all that strict, in fact we''re pretty laid back. Just relax and keep it cool, alright?\n\nPlease enjoy your time here at DreamSpand Gaming. Let us know if we can help you.', 217, 1, '2012-07-04 22:22:31', 46, 'no', ':1:9:2:8:1:8:1:16:1:2:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:23:30:3:32:2:34:1:2:1:1:1:41:42:1:1:2:2:2:2:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:2:1:1:1:1:1:50:1:1:54:1:1:1:55:5:59:60:55', 'What''s expected of you as a member. ** MUST READ **', '2012-10-09 13:52:23', 0, 1, 0, 0, 1, 7887, ':1', '', 'no', 'rules', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
