(197, 'Re: Game Fails', 'Hehe true.\r\n\r\nA few weeks ago I was doing some BF 3 quick matches, and I got paired with the dumbest team I have ever been on.\r\nIt was a fairly tight map, big overall, but It was confined to rooms, and corridors, so lots of explosives were used.\r\n\r\nBut for some reason my entire team had one simple directive for the entire match, "Grenades to the face are how we communicate." All they ever did was throw grenades Everywhere, and at Everything. \r\n\r\nEnemies ahead? Grenades.\r\n\r\nTank ahead? Grenades.\r\n\r\nClearing a room with enemies? Grenades.\r\n\r\nClearing a room with friendlies? Grenades.\r\n\r\nTeammates ahead? Grenades.\r\n\r\nFor 30 minutes all these people did was grenade everything. At one point me and a squad mate was clearing a long corridor that could be used to flank the entire team.\r\nWe had cleared it, we were now holding it. No enemies In It whatsoever. Then i see the orange grenade indicators fly over my head, so I do a 180 and see 3 from my team tossing grenades at an empty corridor, that we owned.\r\n\r\nThat match gave me a headache.', 134, 9, '2012-06-28 18:41:38', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(180, 'Re: Your Ownages', 'Fantastic. \r\n\r\nMost of my ownages were in Battlefield 3. \r\n\r\nOne time I was sniping at extreme ranges. I had set up on an assault ship off the coast of a small island. The enemy had counter snipers deployed on the far side of the map, pretty much the exact opposite side of me. I had my eye on a single sniper, the one farthest away from me, he was pretty good, and got plenty of kills slowing my team way down. We were both on the edges of the map, but he hadn''t seen me.\r\n\r\nI used a bolt action sniper rifle with a 12x zoom scope and a bipod. I wasted 2 shoots trying to correct my aim.\r\nI fired the third shot, and It was a good 3-4 seconds before It hit him.\r\n\r\nBoom. Headshot.\r\n\r\nThe shot was so long my Xbox couldn''t even register it, which blows. But still, I''m fairly confident It was at least 1 Kilometer.', 137, 9, '2012-06-27 22:49:03', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
