(658, 'Re: The Kingdom of the Emerald Castle', '[quote pid=657]\r\n\r\nThe asymmetrical design Is just because I''m far too lazy to start counting how many blocks long and wide the structure is. Also in part because I wanted to make it look like a natural emerald crystal deposit, like it wasn''t too shaped to look man made.\r\nI got the eerie green feel from Minas Morgul in one of the Lord of the Rings movies. Can''t remember which one, but I loved that green light that seemed to come from nowhere. I achieved it by using glow stone blocks hidden behind the emerald blocks. From above It''s obvious how It''s done, but the yellow blocks don''t fit in with the green, which Is why i hid them. \r\n\r\nThe castle itself, without interior, 3-4 hours. I had done a similar style castle in the Hell realm, but I couldn''t do all the things I wanted to with it.\r\nPlus the zombie pigmen kept spawning inside. But after i figured out how i wanted it, time flew by. With the interior, and the now sizable long Bifrost 6-7 hours.', 655, 9, '2012-09-22 15:54:11', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
