(799, 'Re: Maine Democrat Is deemed unfit for office.', 'It''s 99% of the people who play games know what they see is not real, but that small 1% kills it for everyone (pun not intended).\r\n\r\nNewer forms of media and entertainment have always been under fire for any negative influences they could possess. It happened with movies, comic books, and even paperback novels, people said they''d corrupt the minds of their current generation. Just because it''s different and we didn''t grow up with it, then it must be terrible! Makes perfect common sense >_>\r\n\r\nPeople fear what they don''t know and understand, so in our perspective we see their views and choices as stupid and irrational. How do they explain that gaming dominant cultures like Japan have far less violence rates in comparison to countries like the U.S.A? If anything video games are keeping people indoors, which is better than some teenager with nothing to do going out and breaking the law. \r\nIf someone felt so compelled from a video game''s content to imitate it in the real world (i.e. mainly violence) then something was clearly wrong with them before the even first picked up that controller.', 781, 15, '2012-10-06 04:40:29', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
