(816, 'Re: Critique Uncle Java''s Ridiculous Songs!', 'Haha yeah! Those "Wuh-wuh-wuh", "Yo-yo-yo", and "braaaugh" noises aren''t morphed vocal samples. They''re sounds that I synthesized from scratch. Synthesis is a mess to understand...but long story short:\r\n\r\nYou have things called oscillators...they oscillate +move rapidly back and forth  on an equilibrium+ which causes pure tones to be produced +sine waves+. I then take the tones produced and modulate them with the use of filters/envelopes/distortions/reverbs/compressors/EQs/feedback loops/and LFOs +inaudible soundwaves that I use to modulate other soundwaves/parameters+\r\n\r\nIt''s a mess haha. Basically I program it, and then I can push a key on my keyboard to make it go "Blaaaugh, yoyoyoyo, aiaiaiaiaiaiai, wheeeee" etc. Making your owns synths is a science of its very own.', 786, 23, '2012-10-06 18:39:04', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
