(952, 'Re: Game ideas', 'I''ve yet to come across a game that implements RPG, Puzzle, Platformer and Adventure game elements perfectly in one game. Most of the time they just focus on one style while the other styles merely act as add-ons, but don''t enhance much of the gameplay. I don''t mind game style changing to keep things varied and interesting, but I''ve yet to see where all genres are fundamental to the game''s structure.\r\n\r\nMaybe I''m just imagining the impossible.... but if it were real, then shut up and take my money.\r\n\r\n\r\nOther (more specific) ideas I''ve had:\r\n\r\n3D game starring Yoshi, he hasn''t had his own adventure for a while, and all the  solo adventures he''s had are 2D platformers. Yoshi''s been used in Mario Galaxy 2 and Super Mario 64 DS in the 3D environment, so this idea is definitely possible\r\n\r\nSequel for the Mario & Luigi RPG series, the second game (Partners in Time) used baby Mario and Baby Luigi as an extra duo, and the third (Bowser''s Inside Story)  gave the option of parallel storylines. I could see two extra duos, each with their own story that you could follow (and may intersect during progress of the game). Wario & Waluigi as a duo and Peach & Daisy as another pair, separate or interchangable storylines, as well as those two famous plumbers. ', 948, 15, '2012-10-15 05:40:25', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
