(1747, 'Mission 1: Gaming Articles', 'Hey guys, I''ve come up with an idea and I need your help to make this work. You may have noticed that I posted 4 gaming-related news articles in General Gaming yesterday, all from that day. I need the staff members (myself included) to find a web site with very recent gaming news (I''ve found that [url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/]GameSpot[/url] has tons of content to choose from) and post at least one article from there, preferably every day but I know how difficult that can be (although, really, one article per day should be child''s play), so if you have to skip a day or two, that''s fine. [user=16] has already given us plenty (and I mean [i]plenty[/i]) of gaming news in the past, so he is exempt from this if he wishes to be.\n\nYou may post as many per day as you like, there is no maximum limit. It doesn''t have to be college-level writing (I suck at that myself, so asking others to do it is kind of dumb), just well-typed and at least a little thought out. There is no word limit or anything like that. Once you''ve covered the point, you''re good. Just make sure it''s not only a sentence or two long, because that will just look like we don''t even care.\n\nAs long as it''s news about a game, a console, people in gaming (i.e., Miyamoto), accessory, etc (you get the point), it fits. Most of these topics belong in General Gaming, but if you believe it fits somewhere else, that''s completely fine.\n\n[b]**[/b] I know this seems like asking a lot, but if you want this community to flourish, then it can''t be just me. We all have to work together on this. I understand that there may be complications, and that''s okay. Just contact me and we can work something out.\n\nOh, and be sure to include the link to the source of where you found the article. :)\n\nThank you.\n\n[b]Note: [/b] I am not saying "YOU HAVE TO DO THIS" by any means. All that I ask is that in your free time, dedicate a little bit of time to the site with an article or two. :)', 1747, 1, '2013-03-12 22:05:54', 46, 'no', ':1:2:2:1:9:16:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:55', 'Taking the first steps.', '2013-03-13 16:26:41', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 60, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
