(1160, 'Web Site Design Business', 'So a few years ago I mentioned something about setting up a web site design business to my other communities, but some things happened (that we won''t go into) and it never happened. Well, I''ve got everything all set up now, and am awaiting clients. I have not as of yet had any though (mostly because I just set it up last night XD), and would like to get started so I can build up a portfolio. I am very bored and feeling very generous, therefore I will make it half-price to the first two clients to sign-up for it. It''s $80 a page, but click [url=http://www.dreamspand.com/Plans.docx]here[/url] to get a more detailed idea of what you can expect. Remember, first two people get half off the price, that''s for any plan and for any enhancements.\n\nIf you guys could help me out (or find someone who could), I''d really appreciate it. Finding a job in this state is damned near impossible and college is rolling around again, not to mention my grant expired and I have to re-apply, and my mom''s out of work right now due to a fractured shoulder rotatory cuff.\n\nThank you in advance and I hope to have some interested people submit forms to me.\n\n--\n\nTo submit a web site request form, please click the below link:\n\nhttp://www.dreamspand.com/?act=createsite\n\nNote that yes you have to register in order to view that (I had to do that to prevent spam-bots from using it), but registration is completely free and the account is only for convenience purposes. This is also a web site that I created from scratch from the ground up (no programs or helpers used), so you can get a bit of a general idea of what all I can do.\n\nLet me know if you''re interested.\n\n[b]I have also advertised this on Facebook with the price deal so that place counts with this too. In other words, ANYONE who makes it to the first two slots will have the good deal with the price that I mentioned above.[/b]', 1160, 1, '2012-10-28 23:30:58', 46, 'no', ':1:2:34:16:1:9:1:1: