(1753, 'Re: Mission 1: Gaming Articles', 'Other sites to use:\r\n[url=http://www.destructoid.com/]Destructoid[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.gameinformer.com/]GameInformer[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.joystiq.com/]Joystiq[/url]\r\nFor more technical industry news and news from a business perspective, [url=http://www.gamasutra.com/newswire]Gamasutra[/url] is a very good source.\r\nFor Eastern gaming news (Japan, China, Korea) [url=http://www.siliconera.com/]Siliconera[/url] is usually the best bet.\r\nFor direct Playstation news, the [url=http://blog.us.playstation.com/] Playstation Blog[/url] is an easy source of direct news.\r\n\r\nI''ve yet to find a direct news blog for the Xbox360 and don''t feel like looking for a Nintendo blog.\r\n\r\nSites to avoid: IGN, Kotaku, and Inside Gaming from Machinima. These three groups are sensationalist and routinely use yellow journalism to drive up clicks (Kotaku going so far as to make up blatant lies as news). They are [b]NOT[/b] reliable news sources.', 1747, 16, '2013-03-13 04:07:22', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
