(1288, 'Re: What are you playing right now?', 'No, not by far. It''s a really fun game and it has a lot of Halo''s elements, but I think the originals will always be the best. I mean, I say it''s the best right now, but then I''d say five was the best and so on. It''s set up to be a trilogy from the start, unlike its predecessors. I really don''t like the way this story ends in the campaign, though. It''s sad and makes you wonder a bit.\r\n[spoilers]Cortana dies.[/spoilers]\r\nAs far as the game-play goes, it''s definitely awesome, but they removed some of the key aspects that I think really made it.. well, Halo. Namely Firefight, although that one wasn''t too well known and may make a return eventually. I love the game to death though, definitely a good buy. It was a little glitchy at first (as you saw in my topic) but that''s to be expected with any game picked up right at launch, so eh.\r\n\r\nSo all in all, a really, really fun and addictive game, but not the best by far. :p At least to me.', 255, 1, '2012-11-21 03:52:11', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
