(1293, 'OH GOD THE RAPTURE IS BURNING', 'Good afternoon, ladies and gentlemen. Do you remember a man named Harold Camping? In 2011, he held a prediction that the world was going to end. He said Rapture was coming. He said Rapture would come on none other than May 21st, 2011. He said it would [i]begin[/i] to come on May 21st, and that it would properly come on October 21st, 2011.\r\n\r\nIt didn''t. But, on May 21st, I decided to write a journal as if it did, a journal where the sky turns red and cats turn into spiders and every bear is secretly Nyarlathotep incarnate. A journal where the slender man is real and puppets control [i]you[/i]. A journal where England is destroyed within a month, Canada is set on fire after three, all of Asia is set under complete darkness after only a few more weeks, and the entire world is covered in black fire before the world finally ends. Or [i]does[/i] it?\r\n\r\n[url=http://blindrapture.tumblr.com/contents]This, my friends, is [i]OH GOD THE RAPTURE IS BURNING[/i] ("The Rapture Logs" for short).[/url] It''s a four-act epic stream-of-consciousness apocalyptic novel, and I don''t mean "epic" to mean "awesome," I mean "epic" to mean "a story of grand stature." Whether it''s awesome or not is up to you to decide.\r\n\r\n..and okay so if you wanna get technical it has way more than four acts, but I''ve only [i]labelled[/i] four of them. In fact, let me give you the rough synopses for those!\r\n\r\n[b]Act I: (The Coming of) The Four Rakes[/b] Apocalypse NOW! Europe is falling under the control of eldritch beings, and portals to another world are popping up everywhere. Jordan teams up with a lost girl named Donnie, and they are introduced to a rogue''s gallery of horrors as they try to escape the continent.\r\n\r\n[b]Act II: (The Seven Ciphers of) The Blind Man''s Book[/b] Question your answers! America is undergoing many changes politically and demographically, and our protagonists are getting introduced to the rest of the Fears! Can they team up with more protagonists, and is it even possible to find answers at this point?\r\n\r\n[b]Act III: (The Duels of) The Knights of Xanadu[/b] Fate is late! The protagonists are starting to really experience the traumas of the apocalypse! As The Anathema builds up something called "The Neonate" and The Beast''s presence starts to surface, our protagonists are beginning to wonder who the real antagonists are!\r\n\r\n[b]Act IV: The Hunt (of The Beast and The Harlot, The Seven Beacons, and The Terminal Coming of Rapture)[/b] The end is fear! Good portions of the Earth are in Xanadu, and our protagonists have a lot of trouble to figure out before October 21st! Even with the helpful help of Fears Salmacis, Tiresias, and The Musicians, can the heroes beat every single apocalypse coming their way? Make some room, Rapture; The Beast is here!\r\n\r\n[img]http://sunsettersblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/07/beast.png?w=800[/img]\r\n\r\nFinally, the Rapture Logs have a [i]lot[/i] of accompaniment art and illustrations by such lovely artists as Logic, Cadet, Wiratomkinder, The Visitor, and Rappu! That picture right there is by Logic, though you won''t see it in the story until you get to the very end of Act III.\r\n\r\nNow, the Rapture Logs aren''t done yet. We''re about to enter the month of October, around the halfway point of the fourth and final act. But we''d be delighted to have you join us!\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, if you [i]do[/i] decide to read some of the story that''s a little too long and dynamically complicated for me to patiently copypaste into this thread, feel free to give me feedback. :D I will thank you for it forever and ever.\r\n\r\nSo, um. ..enjoy!', 1293, 41, '2012-11-21 16:39:10', 46, 'no', ':1:9:2:41:1:1:1:55', 'Follow me down the rabbit hole if you dare', '2013-05-05 15:37:31', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 149, ':16', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
