(1303, 'Re: Star Wars: The Old Republic', 'I think the best way to implement F2P is to give access to everything to all players, but impose a flat time limit for free players. For example, paid players have full access to the game all day. Free players though can only play for 10 hours weekly but have full access during that 10 hours.', 1297, 16, '2012-11-25 04:23:09', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1304, 'Re: Star Wars: The Old Republic', '[quote pid=1303]\r\n\r\nInteresting idea, but I think that sounds too similar to the parental controls on consoles. \r\n\r\nPersonally I think the Guild Wars 2 model is the only way to go. The entire game is open to everyone, but you can augment, and enhance your game as you go along. GW2 doesn''t offer better gear or weapons, but mostly cosmetic items, super rare crafting items, pets, boosts and some treasure chests with special keys.\r\n\r\nAll of these things don''t take anything away from the game, but only add to it. Whereas SWTOR just crippled every single F2P player.\r\n\r\nBut, I must admit I am considering re-subscribing just to see how the game actually works now.', 1297, 9, '2012-11-25 14:24:38', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
