(1498, 'Re: Violent Videogames and their effects', 'Well the NRA (National Rifle Association) has come out saying [url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/12/nra-violent-movies-video-games/]video games and blood soaked films are responsible for violence.[/url] You know, just like how watching a McDonalds commercial made me fat. About the only thing the NRA gets right is that violence sells, a fact they have managed to exploit and profit immensely off of. \r\n\r\nAlso, [url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/12/21/senator-proposes-bill-to-study-violence-in-games]a bill is being proposed in the Senate to study violence in video games and "other content" and it''s effects on children.[/url] This quote is from the Senator who proposed the bill.\r\n\r\n?Major corporations, including the video game industry, make billions on marketing and selling violent content to children,? Rockefeller concludes. ?They have a responsibility to protect our children. If they do not, you can count on the Congress to take a more aggressive role.?\r\n\r\nTranslation: It''s the governments job to be your child''s parents. \r\n\r\nThe government may try to use video game violence to get out of any real gun law changes as video game violence is a less explosive issue and most who play video games are below voting age. Those sneaky bastards.\r\n', 1488, 16, '2012-12-21 16:55:40', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
