(1654, 'Re: Update: Minecraft Server', '[quote pid=1651]\r\ni dont think "good" is the right word to use...\r\n\r\n[quote pid=1650]\r\nIt really depends on what you want to do for the world. There are plugins that will create an economy for the server (shops and jobs), plugins for protection against hackers and spammers, and plugins that allow you to have colorful texts and messages. \r\n\r\nBut the top three are worldedit, worldguard, and dynmap. Worldedit allows you to drastically change the landscape with ease as well as create massive structures with two clicks and a command. WorldGuard allows you to protect certain areas from other players. for example, it could stop non-admins from breaking blocks within an area, stop fire from growing and burning wood, stop pvp, or make it so that nonadmins cannot enter an area. Dynmap allows you to have a map of the server showing where players are in real time. ', 1633, 34, '2013-02-13 15:24:08', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
