(1719, 'Re: Update: Upcoming Stuff', 'The front page of the site needs to have reviews and articles included instead of just site updates. By that I mean instead of seeing just site updates when they come go to dreamspand.com, they see articles and reviews too. People come for gaming, not whats happening on the site, and that might be the best way to facilitate that. That way, users wont have to mouse over. I guess I''m thinking of a unified feed, instead of just an update feed (unless us staff have been allowed to use the update feed for all posts rather than simple site updates). \r\n\r\nI''m also in favor of a board re-arrangement (I''m always for that). In this case, kill "This Week in gaming". I simply dont have the motivation to do that anymore (too many damn rss notifications). Bump reviews up under general gaming. Take Misc. and put it right above classics. Maybe move forum features as a sub board in the front office. \r\n\r\nAs for content. Quality over quantity for now. Sure, we want more, but it shouldnt be fluff that doesnt really say anything. Lets aim for higher quality content than what most forums provide. I''ve also been trying out a bunch of different games and strange titles (such as a dating simulator starring birds) in the hopes that we can become a diverse forum in gaming tastes. A dude- bro forum simply cannot survive. There are billions of them, so I encourage everyone, step outside of your comfort zone and try out games you may not have tried before. \r\n\r\nWhat I''m saying is, there is a game where your girlfriend is turned into a llama. \r\n\r\nHope my suggestions help. \r\n\r\n', 1718, 16, '2013-03-10 00:50:33', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
