(1859, 'RetroReviews: Grabbed by the Ghoulies[XBOX]', '[center]Grabbed by the Ghoulies Retrospect Review\r\n\r\nGrabbed by the Ghoulies follows a young man named Cooper Chance who sets out to rescue his girlfriend, Amber, from Ghoulhaven Hall. This mansion is full of supernatural creatures, and Cooper will receive help along the way from the many hired hands that work there.\r\n\r\nOriginal Platform: Xbox[/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n-Visuals- 6/10.\r\n\r\nThe game applies a cartoonish style, and therefore doesn?t do a lot to either impress or disappoint.\r\nIt doesn?t look inherently bad or amazing, the style is solid. There is nothing mindblowing about the graphics, but It is consistent.\r\nNo big bugs to report graphics wise.\r\n\r\n-Sounds- 7/10.\r\n\r\nGhoulies has it?s own neat soundtrack, and a fitting theme song. \r\nCreaky doors, scary noises and the monsters all make for a neat, thematic, humorous game. Now, there is nothing to complain about sound wise, but even so it doesn?t necessarily leave any lasting impact. In keeping with the games light-hearted tone, the music is not too deep and dark, but very upbeat and light.\r\nThe characters do not speak, but merely make sounds based on the situations. Their dialogue is presented as text during the story sequences. \r\n\r\n-Gameplay- 7.5/10.\r\n\r\nThe controls always took some adjusting to, but once you get the feel of it everything?s fine. Some things to note that stick out are; the left and right tiggers operate the camera, and attacks are directed with the right analog stick. Getting past these two things shouldn?t be too difficult, and once you do the whole game is great fun.\r\nThere?s a wide variety of weapons always at your disposal. You can fight Ghoulies with almost everything in the room. Often you?re also given mission specific weapons, for example when you have to kill lots of zombies, a water pistol/super soaker will be made available to you, shooting the zombies with it causes them to melt, and if fighting mummies fire is handy.\r\nAlso included are some ?fright? mini games where your character is spooked by something in the environment, and you have to punch in a button combo to prevent passing out.\r\n\r\n-Story- 5/10.\r\n\r\nThe story is simple, humorous and light hearted. It isn?t designed to be a heavy cornerstone of the game, but it does help carry you through particularly challenging levels with it?s simple but well meant humor.\r\n\r\n-Overall- 7.5/10.\r\n\r\nThis game has always been a favorite of mine, but I admit it isn?t for everyone. It?s a simple and funny game not meant to be taken that serious.\r\nIt?ll entertain you through and through if you?re into the genre, but don?t count on something hugely memorable.\r\nEven by today?s standards it remains pretty damn entertaining, and most people would probably find it fun enough to justify purchase. I?d even say it?s suitable for all ages; the humor can be appreciated on different levels by all, the simplicity can appeal to a younger crowd while the challenges can appeal to older audiences.\r\nI recommend it to everyone who?s just looking for something fun to play, but isn?t expecting anything game changing.\r\n', 1859, 9, '2013-03-19 18:36:54', 46, 'no', ':16:34:9:2:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:55', 'Retrospect Reviews #1', '2013-03-19 20:45:39', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 70, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
