(1871, 'Re: The Minecraft Server', 'If we do that, I recommend an actual dedicated server, one that won''t be cut off when a computer shuts off. It will also give us greater freedom and space as we can open multiple worlds within one server as well as have dedicated support. Vibrantblade and I have done a few servers but we always shut them down when we get bored of the game. You can get a solid server for around $8-16 a month, something I''d be okay with helping out with. \r\n\r\n(Also I can actually connect to a dedicated server and help you guys out). Let me know, I would be willing to pay for the first few months since work is giving me 40 hours a week now. I''ll talk to Vibrantblade if you guys are interested. We can also load the map from the current server onto the new server if you all want to go that route and the new server would be available 24/7 (or whenever I''m not detonating 16,000 blocks worth of TNT)', 1870, 16, '2013-03-20 16:37:10', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
