(1882, 'Re: The Minecraft Server', 'Alright, I asked Vibrantblade to write out a nice detailed explanation of the differences between what you have now and what the dedicated can provide. \r\n\r\nHere is what he had to say about it.\r\n\r\n"Exodus Hosting is a good dedicated server that hosts your Minecraft world. You pretty much pay $8 per GB of RAM and they will host it 24/7. With this, you get customer support for problems, no player restrictions, a free MySQL Database, full FTP access, and instant one-click download and installations of plugins. The server can be accessed from a control panel, which multiple people, if the admin so wishes, can go in and read/write server properties.\r\nThe control panel can be set up to have automatic backups of the world(s) just in case something happens.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, a Hamachi can be used to host the server and you can do everything on your own for free. Biggest drawback for this is that the server cannot be run 24/7, harder to install and configure plugins, and you pretty much have to do everything manually, all while using precious computer resources.\r\n\r\nI highly recommend a Hamachi server if the server is going to stay small, where little management is needed. Whereas, if we are going to get bigger, a Dedicated server will be better for it can handle a heavy load of management with ease.\r\n\r\nUnless they have a high tech computer with at least 4GB of dedicated RAM with a strong processor and a good knowledge of server management, they should stick with Dedicated Server"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSo gentlemen, it is up to you. As I said, I will cover the first two months, possibly more but I''m leaving the decision up to you three because this is your thing. Exodus Hosting is what Vibrant and I used on our servers and we liked them over Servercraft Hosting. \r\n', 1870, 16, '2013-03-21 02:50:01', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1883, 'Re: The Minecraft Server', 'Very well, thank you both for your help. Today has been enlightening and we are very seriously thinking about this. I myself am all for it, but this isn''t just my web site, it''s his too, so I have to wait for his official word. He''s just a little afraid of jumping into something this early in the juncture, and I can understand that. I like what I''m hearing though and I really appreciate the hard work you guys have put into this AND the server itself, I''m very pleased. Keep up the hard work guys, you''re all doing great and I''m very proud to have the staff team that I do (I consider VB staff even though he didn''t want to be). You guys are awesome - keep being that way.\r\n\r\nI will talk to Mike more about this tomorrow after he gets off work. Thank you very much again. :)', 1870, 1, '2013-03-21 02:57:52', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1884, 'Re: The Minecraft Server', 'Vibrantblade is a jerk. Don''t be nice to him. I''m never nice to him (except for the fact I bought the idiot a PS2 so he can finally play his beloved Persona 4). And no problemo. Just thought I''d offer you guys an alternative after the issues with the weather and such. ', 1870, 16, '2013-03-21 03:03:52', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1885, 'Re: The Minecraft Server', '[quote pid=1882]\r\nI also like this because it has a MySQL database. If the server is going to have an actual URL, then I can ping it using PHP to tell if it''s up or not, which means that we won''t have to press any buttons on here; it would automatically update (currently, we have to specify if the server is on or off by clicking a button). It sounds like a lot more freedom and, possibly, creativity as to adding in my own coding (this is a huge maybe however).\r\n\r\nWith the server growing more rapidly every day (Me, Mike, vibrantblade, Sam, Jean, Lizzy, Danny, Alaris..) I think it is time to go bigger. So far Mike seems to like the idea and I love it. As I said last night, I will talk to him about this more later when I get the chance.\r\n\r\nThanks guys.', 1870, 1, '2013-03-21 14:26:00', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
