(1919, 'Re: What did you do when you were new to Minecraft?', 'First time i ever played it was Beta. I bought it without knowing much about the game...it looked cool and all the kids were doing it. So i bought it, and started my first survival. Those first few nights were brutal...didnt know what to do, didnt know how to make tools and the type im allowed to make. I stayed near spawn and dug a small 4x4 hole on the side of a cliff. Died a few times in the first week of surviving with little gain...i crafted my tools on my own, i didnt know the recipe for the various tools and items. once i got a foothold after a few nights, i started to mine, developing tunnels to a fort on the top of a nearby mountain. In short, my first time was sloppy, but i finished the job of surviving. ', 1917, 34, '2013-03-24 22:01:27', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
