(1933, 'Automatic Daytime Sensor Setter', 'After a while of constantly setting the world to day time, I figured out a way to make it set day time automatically. I have a daylight sensor behind a sticky piston, and when it''s day time, the piston pushes the redstone block away from the command block. When the piston loses power, the piston retracts, moving the redstone block right next to the command block, setting the time to day automatically. :)\n\nIt works so hey.', 1933, 1, '2013-03-25 13:56:49', 46, 'no', ':1:9:34:2:1:1:1:1:1:1:49:1:5:1:55', 'A way to automatically set the time to day.', '2013-03-25 13:56:49', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 68, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
