(1952, 'Re: Minecraft Server Control Room', 'Will do. Add whom you may, just be careful of Opping them. Make sure they will be active first. \r\n\r\nNow then, we will be using Multiverse to create multiple worlds. The problem with that, is that it has its own options to allow/deny PVP, Mob and Animal Spawning. If the main server settings and the plugin are conflicting, you get the flickering mobs as we did yesterday. So...what has been done to combat this? I  have enabled all three settings on the System Server. SO DO NOT CHANGE THEM. Instead, if you wish to allow/deny any of these three entities, you need to change the settings for Multiverse. This configuration file will be found in plugins/Multiverse-Core/worlds.yml\r\n\r\nThis configuration file is divided into parts, one part for each world. You can change specific settings for specific worlds, so each world can have a sense of individuality. Scroll down to ''world'' section and manually allow/enable any of the three settings, then reload the server. \r\n\r\nIf you are feeling adventurous, play around with the other settings in this configuration file. But make sure you are alone on the server, for you need to reload after every change, and make sure you change the settings back to how you left it. I do not know much about this plugin, so i am eager to see what you guys discover. ', 1940, 34, '2013-03-26 20:06:36', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
