(1985, 'Minecraft Tournaments', '[font=verdana][size=3]Minecraft Tournament[/size][/font]\r\n\r\nBy the order of Lord Vibrant, every able-bodied man and woman will partake in the first ever DreamSpand Minecraft Tournament. \r\n\r\nThis tournament will weed out the weaklings and the untrained. Only the strongest and fittest will survive. The first tournament will be Flatcore Hardcore. Everyone shall be dropped into a flat world with a few trees sprouting about from place to place. PvP will be on, clans shall be made, promises shall be broken. How long will you survive? Will you be stricken by hunger? Will the mob horde pick you off in the night? Or will a fellow contender kill you? Or will you rise from the group, claiming victory? Will you brave the outside world and live off the land? Or will you bunker down, hiding in the ground, waiting for hunger to take your body?\r\n\r\nThe Battlefield: Flatworld, with a few trees littered from place to place. 2 grass blocks high.  \r\n\r\nThe Rules: Nothing is true, everything is permitted. Except for hacks and commands. This will be monitored closely! PvP will be off for the first day and night. Then active after the 1st night. \r\n\r\nWhen: Open for discussion. I would like everyone to participate in this. Might take at most an hour to complete. Due to classes and work, im safe to say after 8pm on any day. But again, open for discussion. \r\n\r\nPrizes: Check back soon!\r\n\r\n-Lord Vibrant', 1985, 34, '2013-04-03 15:53:25', 46, 'no', ':46:34:9:2:16:1:1:1:1:1:1:55', 'Battle of the Cubist', '2013-04-04 19:31:52', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 72, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1986, 'Lucas Arts Closed by Disney', 'A tear for our fallen comrade. Disney, which recently bought all of George Lucas'' assest has shut down Lucas Arts, the game development arm of the Lucas portfolio. Games Lucas Arts is known for include, Star Wars Battlefront, Star Wars 1313, Kinect Star Wars (ouch), and the adventure genre defining game, The Secret of Monkey Island.\r\n\r\nOfficial Statement from Disney:\r\n\r\n[center]"After evaluating our position in the games market, we''ve decided to shift LucasArts from an internal development to a licensing model, minimizing the company''s risk while achieving a broader portfolio of quality Star Wars games. As a result of this change, we''ve had layoffs across the organization. We are incredibly appreciative and proud of the talented teams who have been developing our new titles."[/center]\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rXVT0Khzdhs]Farewell Lucas Arts[/url]. Thoughts go out to  let go.\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.gameinformer.com/b/news/archive/2013/04/03/disney-closes-game-publisher-lucasarts.aspx]Source[/url]', 1986, 16, '2013-04-03 18:03:47', 46, 'no', ':9:16:2:1:1:55', 'N/A', '2013-05-12 14:26:21', 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 68, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
