(1994, 'Re: Minecraft Server Control Room', 'Alright, so there have been a good deal of changes/additions.\r\n\r\n1. [b]Citizens[/b] plugin has been installed. This allows you to spawn NPCs of any mob type, including Players. You can spawn an NPC carbon copy of an actual player of the server and their skin will match their real counter-part''s skin. So if you see another you on the server, don''t freak out, it''s just an NPC. These NPCs can have way-point paths, they can talk, look at you, hold things, act as sentries (supposedly, though I have seen no proof of this yet) and do some other stuff. Refrain from spawning the Ender Dragon as an NPC as it does still cause damage. If you would like to experiment with this, please create a new Multi-Verse world and use it for testing. Just be sure to delete it when you''re done, if you aren''t going to use it again.\r\n\r\n2. [b]Multiverse-Portals[/b] plugin has been installed. With this, you can select a [b]WorldEdit[/b] region to be designated as a portal to a specified world. The survival map and the creative map both now have one that link to each other, as well as [b]Citizen[/b] NPC guards (one of which is a carbon copy of [user=16]). These portals are protected with [b]WorldGuard[/b], and should not be breakable. If they are, then either please fix it yourself (if you''re familiar with the API) or post about it here so that it may be handled.\r\n\r\n3. [b]Spawn[/b] plugin has been installed. This plugin is more for just fun than it is anything else. You can spawn whatever you like, with the amount being up to 100 at a time. Just try not to abuse this, it''s something shiny I added for fun, don''t make me regret it. You can also spawn players or mobs riding other players or other mobs (for instance, a Villager riding a Pig, or solidbatman1 riding vibrantblade18 ). Ask me for the wiki if you''re interested.\r\n\r\n4. [b]BiomeEdit[/b] plugin has been installed. Another one of those shiny things, but useful too, if used correctly. You can use [b]WorldEdit[/b] to select a region and then define it as a biome, or use a "brush" to manually select where you want a specific biome to be, with a specified radius and a specified shape. Has the weather effects and everything.\r\n\r\n5. [b]Notebook[/b] plugin has been installed. Self-explanatory, keeps specific notes about certain users.\r\n\r\nGonna try to lessen the amount of plugins now. While they are really cool (and I am very addicted to them), it''s probably really bad for the server to have all of these.\r\n\r\nLet me know if you are curious about any of these. I will be more than happy to help.', 1940, 1, '2013-04-06 02:31:38', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1995, 'Re: Minecraft Server Control Room', 'Well someone has been busy i see. love the additions, still looking into the Citizens Plugin, we can control certain NPCs using a script. that should be interesting. But as far as you lessening the amount of plugins, it is not needed. The server is meant to hold up much more plugins than what we have. Upgrading the RAM of the server will also make things run smoothly once we get closer to 2 dozen plugins. The only problem i see is if people spam and abuse these plugins. For example, try to not create a dozen NPCs yourself that have no use whatsoever. That adds to the load of the server. Be reasonable when you use these plugins, not trying to be too pushy about this, but we have 9 Admins/OPs.  ', 1940, 34, '2013-04-06 03:48:55', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 34, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
(1996, 'Update: Return of The Minecraft Server', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]We are pleased to present the official return of the Minecraft server. It is no longer on the white-list and is publicly accessible. Before you enter, though, please give our [url=http://www.dreamspand.com/forum.php?act=topic&id=1904]rules thread[/url] a read. We have a number of features and securities installed. These include:\n\n1. [b]Citizens[/b] plugin. Ops can spawn NPC Players, great for roleplaying worlds. These NPCs can walk, talk, hold stuff, execute scripts, etc. We can even make carbon copies of other players.\n\n2. [b]LogBlock[/b] plugin. If a block is destroyed anywhere, it is logged in our SQL database. It will store who did it and what block it was, as well as the date and time of when it occurred. This will protect your creations.\n\n3. [b]Spawn[/b] plugin. This will allow you to spawn any entity, anywhere, up to 100. Please refrain from spawning in survival mode, and refrain from spawning any highly dangerous mobs at all. If you abuse this, you will be jailed and banned. Indefinitely on both accounts.\n\n4. [b]Notebook[/b] plugin. Lets admins and mods keep notes about specific users.\n\n5. [b]WorldEdit[/b] plugin. This one is way too much to explain, simply look it up if you want an explanation.\n\n6. [b]DynMap[/b] plugin. This is for the staff - we can view any part of the map from the browser and see absolutely everything going on.\n\n7. [b]WorldGuard[/b] plugin. This allows us to guard things from other people, from protecting blocks to disallowing even chest access.\n\n8. [b]BiomeEdit[/b] plugin. This will come in handy later and is currently also for the staff, but allows you to change a specified radius into the biome of your choosing.\n\n9. [b]Jail[/b] plugin. Use your imagination on this one - we can jail players for a certain amount of time, and all they can do is move around in their cell.\n\n10. [b]Multi-Verse[/b] plugin. This includes MVP Inventories (separate inventories for worlds) and MVP Portals (travel between worlds using our admin-made, GUARDED portals). \n\nThese are so far the only plugins we have, but that''s likely to change. We''re going to be working on a roleplaying world as well, featuring the NPCs and site-specific lore.\n\nWhen you first spawn in, you will enter Valhalla, a hand-made creation by SammyAxe / Absalon. This was before we had WorldEdit, and it is our most treasured building. It was built by hand in the first few days of opening the server, and it is beautiful. It''s based off of Nordic Mythology, and you will exit it through a rainbow bridge. To your left there will be a portal to the survival map - simply jump in to be teleported. Your inventory and equipment will change to its respective world when you do this. If you walk straight after you first spawn, you will see 10 rules in a row. Please read and obey them or we are going to have a problem. There is a guard walking around the rule signs, carrying a diamond sword. It is an NPC and yes, it is Master Chief from Halo (I named him Guard and the skin applied itself). \n\nThere are a whole lot of other things that you''re just gonna have to see - but don''t be a jerk, and don''t screw up anything that doesn''t belong to you. If you absolutely have to screw something up, then make something really, really nice and either mess it up yourself, or ask us to do it for you. We''ll be more than happy to destroy your crap if you''re the same towards us. Be respectful, and have fun. We currently have no issues or enemies, and I would like to keep it that way. I am open for talking things out, but if you catch an attitude, you''re gone.\n\nThanks and enjoy it![br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 1996, 3, '2013-04-06 22:27:56', 46, 'no', ':2:1:16:1:1:1:1:1:55', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 59, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1997, 'Role-Play Adventure Map', 'Alright guys, huddle around. How would everyone like a Roleplaying Adventure map for the server? It will make things a bit interesting, we could have an economy on it so players can buy and trade, as well as have factions so players could create clans. Servers with RP Adventure maps do have lower turn-over for their players, for it makes things more interesting, compared to vanilla survival. \r\n\r\nIf we do do this, we need a story, a theme. Thoughts on this? I would like everyone to throw ideas around, so we could vote on one. \r\n\r\nMy idea: On an old server, we did a map where there were 3 kingdoms. Each kingdom had its own ''personality.'' We had a dwarf-like city that lived in the mountains, an elf-like city that lived in the woods, and a human-like city that lived in the plains. Each kingdom had its own castle, and surrounding lands. Each player can either join a kingdom, or become outlaws. Each Kingdom had its own set of jobs, the players can choose a job within their kingdom. The Kingdoms could also become allies through trade or become enemies. This is up to the citizens, they decide. \r\n\r\nUnfortunately, my old server did not utilize this for our server died out before we could fully implement it. But we created the kingdoms, made a neutral city in the middle, and layed out plans for politics.\r\n', 1997, 34, '2013-04-07 14:16:28', 46, 'no', ':1:9:34:2:16:1:1:1:1:1:55', 'A theme, a story for it', '2013-04-08 17:43:47', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 88, ':1', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1998, 'Re: Role-Play Adventure Map', 'I''m all for the 3 Kingdoms idea, i think that''s perfect for an RP server.\r\n\r\n', 1997, 9, '2013-04-07 14:29:00', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(1999, 'Re: The Minecraft Server', 'Alright, so the server is now open to the public. This means that people could grief your creations. I highly recommend you to protect your hard-work using WorldGuard. All you have to do is select the region (Two-opposite corners, one on the lowest corner, one on the highest corner) and do //region define <region-name> <players name>\n\n If you do not want to give players the ability to place blocks, do //region flag <region-name> build deny\n\nFor a list of all flags, do //region flag <region-name> g \n\nWhen using this protection, please do not go crazy with it. do not protect meaningless places that are simple and could be created in 10 seconds using WorldEdit. so like protecting an empty sphere that you have no plans on doing anything with in the future', 1870, 34, '2013-04-07 14:45:23', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
(2000, 'Re: Role-Play Adventure Map', 'Well if you know me at all, you''ll know I would normally say Space themed. But that''s not really possible and plus yall got me 2 to .5 (half vote for mine, and half vote for yours). I like the 3 Kingdoms idea. For the name, does Kingdoms Oblivion sound good? Or does that sound cheesy?\n\nedit: If you need help building it, let me know. I need something to do. Plus, I has NPCs. Still learning those but they come in very handy for RP servers. If we can do scripts like it says we can, then we can probably turn them into actual clerks and such. Would be kinda cool.\n\nedit 2.5: Say we do an Econ plugin. This would be purely for the Roleplay world only, right? Or am I missing something? It also would be kinda cool to give it a test run on the creative world, too. I know [user=2] was banking on having the Econ plugin for a few things. I guess that''s something to test one night/afternoon on Skype or something.\n\n^ my dump of ideas', 1997, 1, '2013-04-07 16:12:52', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
(2001, 'Thank you.', 'I''m very lucky to have the staff team that I do. There''s no hierarchical bullcrap, no misunderstandings, we''re good people, all honest and open with each other. There''s no back-stabbing or double-crossing, it''s all just honesty out there in the open. I''m not one for the whole "feelings" thing, believe me, but I just wanted to thank you guys for being so great, to me and the site. Life is still hard for me and right now, as pathetic as this probably sounds, these games are my escape and they''re how I deal with all the pain. It''s a world I can control and build on, I guess that''s what makes me feel so much better. \r\n\r\nBut that''s not the point. I''m just very grateful that I not only have a staff team, I have great friends and I wouldn''t trade them for the world. So uh, you know, thanks. And stuff.', 2001, 1, '2013-04-07 16:20:36', 46, 'no', ':1:16:2:34:1:1:1:1:1:55', 'My gratitude.', '2013-04-07 16:20:36', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 43, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
