(2007, 'Re: Role-Play Adventure Map', 'Actually Alpha, space themed is pretty doable. My old server also made a few planets in "space." Imagine it, a world with no terrain, nothing but empty space. you make spheres of different sizes, each sphere could have its own terrain. Problem with that though, it is a resource hog. not sure why the server will have trouble handling big floating spheres in an empty world rather than a huge terrain world with entities everywhere. When we did it, our CPU usage spiked. \r\n\r\nBut as far as the RP world, yes, we can use an Econs plugin, which we are going to use. It could be used for any world, doesnt have to work for all worlds. But i do like the name Kingdoms Oblivion. Or maybe Obliviated Kingdoms. we shall talk about them on skype if we get the chance. but for right now, if everyone is in favor of it, i can start working on the backbone of the plans. But, again, we need to talk about this over skype. There is a lot of decisions that need to be made to make this work.  So the more people in the skype call, the better. \r\n\r\nAnd Solidbat, we only need more RAM if we get more than a couple of people to join. Maybe 10 solid people. Crap, even with 10 people, 3 kingdoms might be too much...might be 2. we shall see. ', 1997, 34, '2013-04-08 12:59:33', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2008, 'Re: Minecraft Server Control Room', 'It was weird dude, all of a sudden Multi-Verse wasn''t installed, despite the panel saying it was. So I just removed and reinstalled it. Aaaaand then Jean and I met like two Creepers head on. She met one from the back door, I met one from the front, the house was blown up. x_x', 1940, 1, '2013-04-08 15:14:16', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
(2009, 'Re: Role-Play Adventure Map', 'Skype sounds good later today, I''ll sign on and you just call me whenever. Tomorrow I have to go out of town for a week or so but there is Internet down there, just don''t know how good it''s gonna be. \n\nBut yes, Skype sounds good. And I''ve tried the space thing before, I used the bSpace plugin, it was..weird. The Kingdom idea sounds better though. Should be pretty awesome.', 1997, 1, '2013-04-08 15:16:56', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
(2010, 'Re: Role-Play Adventure Map', 'I''m just throwing in my 2 cents:\r\n\r\nFor our first RP adventure i think It''d be good for all of us to start simple, with a "standard" Minecraft map, and go with something classical fantasy (magic, orcs, elves etc.). The reason being, I see this as a stepping stone for the site, and i believe we can lure in a whole variety of new members with an RP server, and we really can''t afford to fuck that opportunity up by jumping in the deep end and hope for the best.\r\nAs awesome and cool as a Space RP definitely Is, it''s not exactly standard, and if it raises the hardware requirements it could scare off potential members.\r\nAnd If it attracts new members, I for one would feel more comfortable managing them in a more familiar environment.\r\nHumans didn''t start with going to the moon, they started by exploring the land, sea, air and then space.\r\n\r\nBut alas, I''m far from an expert on anything Minecrafty, so feel free to correct me if i made any grievous mistakes or assumptions.', 1997, 9, '2013-04-08 16:43:10', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
