(2014, 'Rin''s Mysteries ', 'I have the incredible honor and privilege of announcing the debut visual novel from Project Rin Studios, Rin''s Mysteries (this is a temporary title). Yours truly is part of the core writing team for this project and I am extremely excited about the direction the Project Rin team is taking. Enough rambling, here is the first tease I''m allowed to share.\r\n\r\n[center][i]"They''re onto us." A worried voice broke the silence. "Someone outside has gained access to the files. We have to get out." \r\n"But what about the artifact!" another voice exclaimed.\r\n"It''s already been decided. We have no choice..." the voice trailed off.\r\n\r\n\r\nRin had been alone for as long as she could remember. After her parents died in an accident, she had lived with her grandfather at the shrine. Her only comfort is her best friend Minchi who has been with her since she was a young child. Rin had never been allowed to leave the Shrine, until one day her grandfather asked her, "Rin, how would you like to go to school?"\r\n\r\nKatsuo has never been able to fit in. Always moving from one town to another, he had never been able to settle down and make friends. "This time, it will be different," he muttered standing at the bottom of the hill leading to the shrine. "Just give her the survey, introduce myself, and don''t do anything stupid." As he climbed the steps he heard what sounds like a girl singing. "Shes singing?" he wondered as he reached the last steps. As he looked around his gaze was drawn to a girl sitting under a tree with her eyes closed, softly singing to herself. \r\n[/i][/center]\r\n\r\n\r\n[center][b]Early Concept Art[/b][/center]\r\n[spoilers][center][img]http://i984.photobucket.com/albums/ae324/solidbatman/Art_Moo_Sketches_InitialIdeas_edit_commentary_zps25751028.png[/img][/center][/spoilers]\r\n\r\nAs part of the core writing team, I will continue to bring Dreamspand exclusive insights into the visual novel and I will provide more information as I am allowed. A link to the developer blog will be coming soon.', 2014, 16, '2013-04-08 18:05:46', 46, 'no', ':16:1:34:9:2:1:1:1:1:1:55', 'Working Title ', '2013-04-08 18:05:46', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 75, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2016, 'Minecraft Server', 'Okay, so as you all know, we are creating a Role-Play Adventure Map. The idea that was most popular was to have Three Kingdoms. Each Kingdom will have its own class that makes it unique from the others. This is where you guys come in, we need to vote on these 3 classes. We have 6 to vote on, if you have ideas on any of them, let me know and i will add them to the vote. The names are not permanent, nor are the traits of each kingdom, we will change them a bit to meet needs. But what makes them different from each other? Well then...\r\n\r\n[list]\r\n[*] Woodsmen are found in the forest biome. They are great builders, they have the ability to clear down forests and create great structures in their place. They are fierce fighters as well, their tool creations are unmatched, and some say, they have powers. They equip the Kingdoms with wood and tools. \r\n[*] Plainsmen are found in the plain biome. They are farmers and live off of the ground and the livestock they attend. They equip the Kingdoms with farmed food, and meat off of their livestock. They are neutral, and hold no ill will towards others, unless they are provoked and attacked first. Then, they use their fierce archery skills to defend. \r\n[*] Snowmen are found in the snow biome. They are peace keepers of the Kingdoms, scribesmen, and scholars. They are majestic people and seldom let people on their lands. not much is known about them, other than they are slow to anger, and when they were, a war broke out and left forests burnt and mountains blown to ashes. Some say, they are aided by spirits of their ancestors. \r\n[*] Nomads are found in the desert biomes. They are simple living people that keep to themselves. A person''s wealth is defined by the wells they have. They are expert sculptures and build their houses out of sandstone. Rich clear glass, glass that is filled with light, and sculpted sand litter their Kingdom. They have a knact for glowstone, and are always on the lookout for glow dust. They often become mercenaries to get more from the other kingdoms. \r\n[*] Miners are found in mountainous biomes. They are proud people, and are skillful in the works of stone. Their cities lie deep in the mountains, protected by thick walls of stone. Gold, Silver, Diamond, and Iron litter the city walls. their lust for jewels is unmatched and usually horde them and trade very little to the outside world. They create tools made out of diamond and gold, their opponents in battle are awestruck by the glittering waves of soldiers, they see nothing but glitter before they are struck down. \r\n[*] Junglers are found in the jungle biome. They are savages and brutes. Their actions are not bound by any laws. And attack any and all trespassers. From the history of the world, the junglers never created cities, they kept to ancient structures that were built from something that is now extinct. However, a few years ago, they started building a city. What caused them to assemble? The Snowmen are clueless, but, reports say that strange beings were found in the village, trading cocoa beans for carrots. \r\n[/list]\r\n', 2016, 34, '2013-04-09 00:26:34', 46, 'no', ':9:2:34:16:1:1:1:1:1:1:55', '3 votes per person, choose three', '2013-04-09 01:05:02', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 113, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
