(2023, 'The Three Kingdoms', 'Alright, so the votes are finally in!\r\n\r\nWe are tied with Woodsmen, Miners, and Snowmen! Thank you everyone who voted! (which is literally everyone) Now we can finally start to make this happen. \r\n\r\nRight now, I am at a loss as to whether to make this world in a Large Biome, or Regular map. But before we can make this decision, we need to thoroughly explore the Kingdoms map (large biome), so we can use dynmap to see where we can put the center of the kingdoms. The Woodsmen live in the forest biome, the Miners in mountainous region, the Snowmen in snowy biome, and the village in a plain biome. \r\n\r\nThe good thing about large biomes, is that it will make things a bit more interesting. Kingdoms will be far apart, so each kingdom can control large portions of land. This is good when we become a large server. However, each kingdom needs to be connected to the village, so it will be better if we can get all four biomes to be next to each other, for a road needs to be built. The good thing about a regular map, is that the kingdoms will be closer together, promoting a faster paced game. If things get too close, we can choose a farther biome. So choose the next closest snow biome, for example. So think about this, let me know what you guys think. but either way, we need to explore the maps before we build anything. \r\n\r\nIm trying to find a way for dynmap to show unaccessed portions of the map automatically. These portions are black, for those chunks have not been loaded, for no one has been there yet. If i do find a way, then everything will be simple. \r\n\r\nUntil then, if any of you have free time, we need to start exploring the Kingdom world. As you can see on dynmap, i already explored most of the jungle biome. We dont need to fill out everything, but we need to at least get the perimeter of each biome, to get a glimpse. \r\n\r\nSorry for the big wall of text. \r\n\r\nOh and we need Kings. So choose one of the kingdoms if you are up for the challenge. if two people want to do the same one, then the PvP arena in creative mode will settle the winner. \r\n\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nA bit of info for each kingdom, subject to change, please discuss\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nWoodsmen are hunters and gatherers. They are also lumbermen, they clear down forests to make room for expansions. They live in log cabins and are expert woodusers. They can craft the finest wooden tables, in all the lands. They are fierce fighters, they are swordsmen and can tame dogs to help them fight in battle. They supply the world with wooden products and the finest steak. \r\n\r\nMiners are builders and strong. They are usually found in their mines, looking for gold and diamond. When they are outside, it is mainly on the road to the village to sell what they have. Their city is located deep within a mountain, the rocks carved to marvelous stone, glittered with diamond and gold. They are rowdy fighters, preferring axes and hand-to-hand combat. Their repair skills are unmatched and provide services for the world. However, they do not welcome those who trespass into their lands.\r\n\r\nSnowmen are gentle folk. They are found in the snow biome, often living with the earth. Their houses are made out of ice that never melts, and hardly break down trees, but instead live in them. They are diplomats, scholars, scribesmen, and potion masters. It is rare for them to go to war, they usually try to talk down the other kingdoms out of war, but when they do fight, they use their bows and potions. Their archers are the best in all the lands, their potions are said to heal and to poison. The last war that they have fought, left forests burned and mountains to dust. ', 2023, 34, '2013-04-10 18:49:34', 46, 'no', ':9:16:34:1:2:1:1:1:1:1:55', 'Official discussion thread', '2013-04-16 05:44:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 34, 380, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2028, 'Re: The Three Kingdoms', 'I say go for it. i incorporated the jungler''s use of potions to the snowmen. but whatever you can make work, while still giving everyone a unique sense, then go for it. and remember, we are not going to be calling them woodcutters, snowmen, etc. The miners could be called the Jiralhanae for example. (if anyone knows what that is, i would be so proud)', 2023, 34, '2013-04-11 13:07:46', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
