(2052, 'Re: The Three Kingdoms', 'Here''s the revised Kingdom descriptions:\r\n\r\n\r\n?  Woodsmen are found in the forest biome. They are great builders, they have the ability to clear down forests and create great structures in their place. During the war the Woodsmen formed the backbone of the Kingdoms armies. After the war they resumed their old ways, and helped rebuilding their own, and the other Kingdoms. They are fierce fighters as well, their tool creations are unmatched. They equip the Kingdoms with wood and tools. \r\n\r\n?  Plainsmen are found in the plain biome. They are farmers and live off of the ground and the livestock they attend. They equip the Kingdoms with farmed food, and meat off of their livestock. They are neutral, and hold no ill will towards others, unless they are provoked and attacked first. Then, they use their fierce archery skills to defend. In the Big War their Kingdom was lost, and the survivors banded together with outcasts of the other Kingdoms to form the central Village.\r\nAfter the war, the lack of food they used to provide resulted in hunger for all the kingdoms.\r\n\r\n?  Snowmen are found in the snow biome. They are peace keepers of the Kingdoms, scribesmen, and scholars. They are majestic people and seldom let people on their lands. not much is known about them, other than they are slow to anger, and don?t like to enter a war they haven?t already won. Some say, they are aided by spirits of their ancestors. \r\nDuring the Big War they provided potions to the Kingdom armies, and had to rely heavily on Nomad Mercenaries for front line soldiers. After the war they retreated to their great halls, and distanced themselves from the aftermath, while looking into the Junglers reasons for attacking.\r\n\r\n?  Nomads are found in the desert biomes. Before the war they were a majestic people, building great pyramids out of glass and sand, their kingdom was said to be the most beautiful one. When the war broke out they faced most of the initial attacks, and much of their Kingdom was destroyed. They began to hire themselves out as mercenaries, and helped the other Kingdoms win. After the war they were unable to fully rebuild their cities, and resorted to living a Nomadic life, travelling around the desert plains, offering their services to whomever could find them. Since the war they have wanted a larger role in the Kingdoms politics, and hope to one day rebuild what was lost. \r\n\r\n?  Miners are found in mountainous biomes. They are proud people, and are skillful in the works of stone. Their cities lie deep in the mountains, protected by thick walls of stone. Gold, Silver, Diamond, and Iron litter the city walls. their lust for jewels is unmatched and usually horde them and trade very little to the outside world. During the war the Miners remained neutral, and profiteered immensely by supplying the other Kingdoms with weapons and armor. Later in the war, the Junglers managed to crack their stone cities, and forced them into the war, and their armies were capable but few in number. After the war they resumed living as recluse, while selling stones and iron to the other Kingdoms.\r\n\r\n?  Junglers are found in the jungle biome. They are savages and brutes. Their actions are not bound by any laws. And attack any and all trespassers. Very few records exist that give any indication of how their society works, and no attempts have been made to contact them in centuries. They started the Big War by launching assaults on the Nomads, and Plainsmen, and proceeded to destroy much of the Kingdoms before they were finally defeated and pushed back into the dark, deep jungle.\r\nThe Snowmen have begun studying them intently, and hopes to find out what caused the attack, and how they came to be so powerful.\r\n\r\nI need criticism and thoughts, and of course the Kings of the respective Kingdoms can throw some feedback at me, and possible feats you''d like for your kingdom.\r\n', 2023, 9, '2013-04-13 20:55:35', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
