(2082, '1.6 Snapshot', 'So I''m trying out the 1.6 snapshots and the new launcher to see how things are coming together, and so far I''m very impressed.\r\n\r\n* Horses can be spawned using a Horse Spawn Egg, and will sometimes produce a donkey.\r\n\r\n* There are many different skin textures for horses.\r\n\r\n* There are skeleton and zombie versions of horses.\r\n\r\n* To tame a horse, you right-click it with an empty hand, and it will likely buck you off. Giving it apples, sugar or wheat will help speed up both the growth process and the taming process. Eventually the horse will let you stay on it. At this time, you press the Sneak key to dismount your house, and may place a horse saddle on it. You can then control the horse with the WASD keys (or whatever you have set for your directional keys), once you have re-mounted it. While riding a tamed horse, your hunger and health bars are replaced by the horse''s. You automatically climb one-block-tall areas, and can jump over I think four blocks at a time. You start off at a somewhat fast walk, but then speed up a considerable amount.\r\n\r\n* Hay bales have also been added to the game, which horses seem to eat. They will likely be crafted using wheat, but this is unconfirmed.\r\n\r\n* Horse armor has also been added to the game.\r\n\r\n* When a horse wearing a horse saddle dies, it will drop a regular saddle (such as those found in dungeons and other treasure chest areas).\r\n\r\n* Horses (as well as other regular animals) can be tied to a fence using a rope/leash, and can also be "walked" around using this method. This does not work on Villagers.\r\n\r\n* Carpets have been added, which are like wool but a lot smaller.\r\n\r\n* New launcher has been released. This allows you to store multiple accounts, as well as multiple versions of the game.', 2082, 1, '2013-04-19 16:41:40', 46, 'no', ':2:1:9:46:1:1:1:55', 'New things so far.', '2013-05-03 18:54:33', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 101, '', '', 'no', 'minecraft, 1.6, snapshot, test', '', ''),
