(2086, 'Discussion Needed', 'Before I start, I mean no disrespect to anyone on these forums. This is purely a discussion that I feel needs to happen to clarify things for myself.\r\n\r\nI''ve been creating a lot of articles and content for this forum. My early stuff was easy stuff that I could pump out in 30 minutes to an hour. However, I have been putting a lot more effort into my writings and now I easily spend an entire day working on one article (longer if you count the brainstorming and planning). For example, my Clannad review took around an entire day to write, and about a week of gathering my thoughts and planning. In other words, I put a lot of effort into my works and with that, a lot of pride goes into them as well. \r\n\r\nIt pains me to then see no comments, and barely any views on these writings. After some thought, I realized that my gaming tastes, while varied, to primarily lie in the more niche, less popular genres while the majority of members here are more into the popular, better selling genres and games. In other words, I feel like I''m writing for the wrong audience. \r\n\r\nThere is a reason though, that I won''t change what I write about. Because the Minecrafts, Battlefields, Mass Effects have been written to hell and back again. Everyone hears about it, and because of that, it is always being written about. I don''t feel the need to write about those games because almost everything to say about them has already been written.\r\n\r\nI want to continue my writing, but when I post on here and see no discussion on my writings, it drains any motivation I have to continue. \r\n\r\n\r\nSo I ask you guys this.... do you want to be a more western, pop-culture gaming forum, or do you want a more niche, "unique" gaming forum with content that isn''t necessarily the most popular, but content that is hard to find anywhere else. \r\n\r\nI am not asking you guys to change anything. I am not demanding anything. \r\n\r\nI simply want to know what direction you guys want to go. I want to know, am I writing for the wrong audience? \r\n\r\n\r\nEdit: No I am not crying for comments, or asking for them. I want to know the direction you guys want to take and if you even find my writings interesting. ', 2086, 16, '2013-04-23 01:48:56', 46, 'no', ':1:34:2:1:1:1:1:55', 'N/A', '2013-04-25 16:57:41', 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 129, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2102, 'Re: Discussion Needed', '? You mean you haven''t done the BF3 thing yet? Huh... then I wonder where these two or three new members came from all of a sudden. Ah well. I''m not gonna complain. XD\r\n\r\nAnd yeah I''m mad at myself too. Also I agree we need to work on advertising, but I was hoping you guys could work on that while Mike and I work on the site. I''ve already asked him to do a sketch of the new home-page for me that would work, since he''s good at that stuff. He''s my designer guy.', 2086, 1, '2013-04-24 16:06:42', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2087, 'Re: Discussion Needed', 'Well, as the one who actually built the site and is paying for it, I can say that I want the site to not be single-themed. In other words, I want it to have a little bit of everything, and you do that well. I am sorry for the lack of comments; it seems that not a lot of posting goes on at this site at all. And yes, going into the mainstream stuff would suck because [i]everybody[/i] does that.\r\n\r\nI have tried and tried to get more people posting content and replying to it and all of my efforts have been in vain, you are the only one that actually posts the content. Some others do, maybe every few weeks or months, but not like you do, and I''m very happy to have you as part of the team because you do your job and you do it well. If comments and readers are what you''re wanting, then I certainly can try harder to do that for you, because you cared enough to try hard for the site and that''s all I''ve been asking for.\r\n\r\nI agree that it''s rather disheartening to work very hard on something and have people not notice it. Take the site for example: I built it by hand, from scratch, and had it released in less than a month. It has state-of-the-art security and some fancy features that not a lot of places have, but it''s as dead as a doornail. It''s one of those things you just kinda learn to live with.\r\n\r\nAt my last community, I was a little bit bossy, and I made a vow to myself not to do that here. If they don''t want to post anything, I''m not going to force them to. I''m not saying you are, by any means, don''t get the wrong idea; I''m just saying that I''m not gonna be all authoritative on my team to get them to post. With all that''s going on in my life right now, I have absolutely no reason or right to point fingers at anyone else.\r\n\r\nAnyway, back to the point, I know you work hard, and you''re great with content, you really are. It''s kind of awesome to see all of the unique stuff you post, and while some of it is kind of odd to me, it doesn''t mean it is odd to others. It draws in a new, unique type of crowd, and that is what I want. Unique is good, because people are always looking for something different and I believe that straying away from the mainstream stuff is always good. It works in real life and it will work here too.\r\n\r\nSo my personal opinion is this: I''m disappointed that not a lot of staff members post and that it''s not often when they do. It makes the whole site look bad when the mods and admins hardly ever post, and yes, I can admit I''m amongst that group. I have the same motivation problem that you do: if I don''t see anyone else trying, it makes me feel like me trying would be pointless. Take the articles I tried to do for example, I did a bunch of those every day, and maybe one or two of the staff members did it once or twice, after I asked nicely a couple of times. I exempted you from that because of all the hard work you''ve done, you''ve clearly shown that you care and that you want the site to move in a good direction. You''re doing a fantastic job.\r\n\r\nAs for the others, I''m sorry to say this, but work harder. The Minecraft server is fun and all, and it''s distracted all of us, but the site is important too. We can''t forget about what the server was originally [i]for[/i]. Yes, I know I sound like a hypocrite right now, and I''m not gonna use the loss I''ve went through as an excuse (or any of the other crap going on right now), but as I''ve said many times before (and as solidbatman is saying now), we cannot be the only ones trying. That is not going to work. I did the majority of the work, hell, I did ALL of the work at my last two communities, simultaneously, when I was a young teenager. I was hoping that starting off with an actual team would provide even better results, but I guess I was wrong.\r\n\r\nI''m not trying to step on anyone''s toes or come off as a jerky, power-hungry savage, but come on guys, we can do so much better than this. We even got a new member yesterday, if anyone other than me and Mike even cared to notice. The games are fun but we have to remember what they were originally for. We need more posts, guys. I can ask my friends to post some stuff every so often that aren''t staff and are members here, but it''s not gonna look very good to anyone if we aren''t helping them.\r\n\r\nSo I don''t know about you, but starting tomorrow when I get back home, I''m going to post some stuff, I don''t care if it''s late at night, I''m doing something. You don''t have to start tomorrow or in the middle of the night, nothing like that, but don''t let me do this alone. I don''t wanna make any changes, but I will if I have to. And I don''t wanna go through that hell again.\r\n\r\nSo guys, help me and Bradley out. We''re trying hard, and you guys need to try too.', 2086, 1, '2013-04-23 04:00:47', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
