(2118, 'Update: Skin issue has been fixed.', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]It came to my attention yesterday that the site had no default skin displaying while logged out, it was simply a white page. Mike showed me this while he was sketching the new interface and testing things out and I have fixed the problem. The Halo: Infinity skin is now the default, and I intend to work on more. This was likely a large portion of why not a lot of people signed up or stayed. More fixes and additions to come. Part of the stuff I intend to add is going to make adding content easier and more flexible, for both members and staff.[br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 2118, 3, '2013-04-25 18:30:42', 46, 'no', ':1:2:1:1:1:1:55', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 60, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2119, 'Let''s talk about content.', 'What kind of content did you guys have in mind? Do you want posts, pages, what? I just need to know more specifically what you guys think we should do. We need something unique to set us apart, and we need to come up with ideas. I''ll start.\r\n\r\nWhen I first made the site, I was thinking we could, occasionally, have community game nights. That''s been an issue lately because not everyone has something that everyone else has. We''ve been looking into Steam, however, and there are some pretty cool, free-to-play games. Warframe and Star Conflict are pretty cool and straight-forward, I''m sure there are many others, too. We could announce game nights every other week or so and have the community join in as an entire group. This was just one idea I had.\r\n\r\nMike had an idea last year about producing videos to go with X-Box 360 achievements, or just to have a video section of the site to entertain our viewers (all 3 or 4 of those non-members!). We just can''t do this ourselves yet cause we lack the tech we need, and we don''t have the money to get it right now.\r\n\r\nSo now I wanna hear from you guys. Throw me some ideas, give me something you think we should start doing, you name it..aaaaand go!', 2119, 1, '2013-04-25 21:05:14', 46, 'no', ':1:34:9:16:2:1:1:1:1:55', 'N/A', '2013-04-26 14:08:48', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2120, 'Re: Lets talk about content.', 'When I say content, I''m talking about original articles or reviews. Opinion based pieces. Because if we try for a more news oriented approach, we''ll fail. We dont have the sources, nor the user base to do that (my daily news thing was a terrible idea in hindsight). Once we have a solid reader base, spread out and experiment with some of these other ideas. So sticking to editorials and discussion on major news is what I think would work best. Ignore the extra stuff. ', 2119, 16, '2013-04-26 03:26:51', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
