(2123, 'Update: New redesign of homepage.', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]The main home page of the site has been slightly redesigned and repositioned a little bit. Affiliates also now display on the homepage, as well. Adding articles and reviews (as well as reading them) should be easier than ever, now. I''m not done with this, either. I intend on making it even more user-friendly, but that will have to be after next week because starting tomorrow I''m going to be out of town for a week and unable to work here. I trust that, in that time, the staff team will be adding content to the forums and the homepage (copy and paste from one to the other if you want to, staff).\n\nHopefully I''ll have time to add in an article or two myself today amidst packing.[br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 2123, 3, '2013-04-26 15:52:59', 46, 'no', ':9:1:2:1:1:1:1:55', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 50, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2124, 'How To Add Pages And Games', 'Adding a page is really simple, and I''ve made it a little bit simpler now (though some may argue differently but eh).\r\n\r\nAlright, so, say you want to add in an article to the homepage. First, click on [b]Create Page[/b], and this will take you to the right screen. Next, type in the name of the page (what will display in the title bar) and then the page ID in its field (so the site knows what ID to pull data from). After that, type your content, and BEFORE you post it, select it all and copy it to a Notepad file, just in case. This ensures that you don''t lose all of your information! Alright, now, before you post it, be sure to change the category from None to [b]Articles[/b]. You can always go back into the page and change the category later if you mess up, but it''s really simple to get it right the first time.\r\n\r\nIt works similarly for the other pages, too. The only difference is that you just change the category, to say, Reviews, Gaming, Site Info, Community, Platforms, etc. And that''s how you add a page. Yep, it''s really that easy.\r\n\r\nManaging user submissions is also really simple. If a user submits a page, then the Manage Submissions will have the number of submissions by it (under the banner on the home page). You can view a list of all of the submissions this way. Click on the page and look it over. If you think it''s good, click on [b]Approve[/b]. This will automatically add it to the [b]User Content[/b] category. If you don''t like it, then click on [b]Deny[/b]. This will simply delete the page forever. Note that the site does log these actions for security purposes.\r\n\r\nNow, adding consoles and games is a little bit more complicated. First, what you wanna do is click on the [b]GMS Console[/b]. GMS stands for Game Management System, and it is how the site works.\r\n\r\n[b]Adding A Platform Key (Gaming Console)[/b]\r\nClick on [b]Platform Keys[/b]. This will take you to the list of consoles. On the top right hand corner of the table, click on [b]Add Key[/b]. For the Key ID, type something short and sweet. This is just a reference code and can be anything you want it to be, but it would be very good form to shorthand the name of the console. In the console name field, type the console''s name (who saw that one coming?). Click on [b]Create Key[/b] and then you''re done.\r\n\r\nOnce you''ve made the key, we need to do something with it. Click on [b]Create Page[/b] up top. Alright, now do the usual page name and ID stuff, but make it relevant to whatever console you''re making it for (i.e., if the key was Atari, I''d make that the page name too). Now then, the page content is really simple. This is where the site does most of the work for us. Now then, still using the atari key as an example, you''d type just this in the content box:\r\n\r\n{platform-id: atari}\r\n\r\nWith atari, of course, being the Key ID of the platform key. Now, before you click Save, change the category of the page to Platforms. Then click on [b]Save Page[/b] and you''re done. If the key is new, then no games will be listed under the name of it yet. Notice, though, how it automatically generates a list. This saves you the trouble of adding them all in yourself. Now we want to add a new game for this console.\r\n\r\n[b]Adding A New Game[/b]\r\nClick on [b]GMS Console[/b] up top. Then click on [b]Manage Games[/b]. You will see a list of every single game that has been added thus far. Now click on [b]Add Game[/b]. A long list of fields will be displayed on this screen. Fill in the required information (preferably WITHOUT copying and pasting information from somewhere else because we don''t want to get sued), and give a good, detailed description about the game. Once you''ve finished filling out the information, select what platform the game is on. So, if you were adding an Atari game, you''d select Atari. Notice how it''s already there, since we defined it as a platform key already. Now click on [b]Done[/b]. Now then, click on the [b]Consoles[/b] page. Since created an Atari page, it was added to the list of Console pages. Click on the name of the console you added, in this case, Atari. Now, instead of saying "No games were found," it will list all of the games that you''ve added under that platform key. Simple!\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about how to add or do something, then please ask me here and I will be more than happy to help.', 2124, 1, '2013-04-26 15:59:54', 46, 'no', ':1:9:2:16:1:1:1:1:55', 'Easy peasy lemon squeezy.', '2013-04-26 15:59:54', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 40, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
(2125, 'Valve Offers Subscription Through Steam', 'Valve, creators of Half-Life and Portal, now allows its users to sign up for subscription plans. The very first supported title for these subscriptions is MMO Darkfall Unholy Wars. A subscription for this game will run around $14.95 USD per month. Though users can sign up for and cancel subscriptions, a gift subscription to others is not currently applicable. Subscriptions to game such as EVE were available before yesterday, but the difference is that the subscriptions can now be managed through the service.\r\n\r\nSource: http://www.gamespot.com/news/subscription-plans-now-available-on-steam-6407538', 2125, 1, '2013-04-26 16:36:57', 46, 'no', ':46:2:16:9:1:1:1:55', 'Half-Life and Portal creators offer Steam subscriptions.', '2013-05-07 00:07:30', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 77, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
