(2135, 'Re: So.', 'I will strive to post thoughtful threads, as much as i can. This week just turned out a lot busier for me than i anticipated. A lot of schools here had canceled classes for the past month, and 3 out of 4 of my classes were among them. This is the first week with classes resumed, and we''re less than a month from exams, so they''re throwing a lot of stuff at us. \r\n\r\nThe articles I want to write are really long and complex in nature, the first one planned is about the two and a half something years i played World of Warcraft, and i really want to nail that one, so I have to write notes, and script a few things to make it up to the standard i want to set for me.\r\n\r\nIn short, i just need a little more time to start tossing up regular articles, and good posts. I''m aiming to set a high standard for this place, and I''d hate to screw it up.', 2132, 9, '2013-05-01 17:45:03', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2137, 'Re: Tattoos?', '[quote pid=2073]\r\n\r\nThe great thing about tattoos is you don''t have to settle for one motive, you can have Yuko, Halo, Skulls and Butterflies in the same one. In fact that''d probably be pretty badass.\r\n\r\nBut of course if you don''t feel good about getting one, you shouldn''t. Personally i think tattoos should be personal, and have some meaning to them.\r\nA buddy of mine just gets tattoos for the hell of it, within a few months (literally less than 6) he got, on his arm, raspberries, a mario mushroom, a small whale, colored an old tattoo and an owl. For no other reason than he just wanted a sleeve tattoo, and i just think that that was a huge waste of time and money.', 2069, 9, '2013-05-02 14:25:44', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
