(2149, 'Re: So.', '[quote pid=2148]\r\n\r\nForgive me if I''m a little bit hesitant to put a ton of effort into my writing here. I mean, remember how I was really the only one writing original content for long periods of times, minus a few days here and there where you called for more activity? Or did anyone notice how a certain piece of mine got well over 6,000 views and absolutely no reaction from the forum? \r\n\r\nSo yes, I really don''t want to spend my entire day off writing when I can''t even tell if the people here care about it. Which is why I just want to wait and see if this is sustained, or if it''s just another passing spike in activity, which has happened a couple of times now. ', 2132, 16, '2013-05-02 21:20:23', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2150, 'Re: So.', 'Bat: I''m with Alpha on this, we shouldn''t have to write our stuff because someone else did, we should write what we can, independently. If we don''t It''s just going to end up in a vicious circle that''ll only get harder to break.\r\n\r\nAnd It''s not like we have to pour everything we got into every review or article we do, we just have to make some effort, and post it so we stay fresh. Nobody is saying you have to spend a day writing your stuff, but If that''s the way you want to do it, you can''t really blame us for not wanting to spend a day writing as well. That''s your choice, you can spend an hour on it if you want to.\r\n\r\nJust my opinion on that subject.\r\n\r\nAnd i also feel like we should be pouring more effort into advertising. I mean, at this point we''re still just like 7 people, so all the things we post here, It''s just like we''re posting it for each other, and we should be making these things for the members, members that we kinda need more of.\r\nRight now we''re relying on each to keep us motivated to make stuff, but our members are the ones who should be keeping us going, and investing some time and effort into getting more of them seems like the right thing to do at this juncture.\r\n\r\n', 2132, 9, '2013-05-02 21:46:08', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
