(2209, 'Re: Bioshock Infinite Review', 'Well then, I must say, this is well done, simply breathtaking. I can feel your enthusiasm throughout this review. Heck, it got me on the edge of my seat, my hands on my chin, while stroking my beard. I am not a fan of the Bioshock series, but you got me to think about trying this game out. So, I applaud you. \r\n\r\nNow for the game, I like how it is set into an American Patriotic theme. Looks like three of the founding fathers, a breathtaking scene might I also add. The liveliness of the city is probably what interests me the most. I like those open, unique games that always remind the player that they are playing amongst others, that you are just one piece in a world filled with many. Also heard you can interact with some of the citizens, especially one about a woman with a tally mark board...not sure what is up with that. \r\n\r\nSo I think this article won over one gamer, I shall think about buying this to try it out, especially if it deserved a 10/10 from you. ', 2208, 34, '2013-05-13 15:24:43', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
