(2239, 'Xbox Reveal', 'Just a few minutes ago, Microsofts new Xbox was revealed, and It is called the Xbox One.\r\n\r\n[img]http://s.pro-gmedia.com/videogamer/media/images/pub/605x/xbox_one111.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nThe new console is aiming to be a unified entertainment system, providing you with access to gaming, TV, internet, sports, music and more. \r\n\r\nIt gives users instant access to all of the above. Using simple voice commands, you can switch almost instantly between games, TV shows, movies, internet browsing, and music. All without having to close one program, and start up another.\r\n\r\nUsing voice commands you can also navigate the menus, answer Skype calls, and more.\r\n\r\nThe controller also underwent a redesign, and will have "16% longer battery life". It also has a " built-in rumble system called ''Impulse Triggers''", allowing developers to program feedback directly into the triggers.\r\n[img]http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5a/Xbox_One_Controller.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nA redesigned and improved Kinect sensor is also bundled with the new Xbox.\r\n\r\n"The device will run three operating systems; Xbox OS, the Windows NT kernel and another OS that will allow the other two operating systems to communicate." From my understanding, this it what allows the Xbox One to switch so fast between programs.\r\n\r\nDuring the first year of Xbox One''s launch, Microsoft with release 15 console exclusives, 8 of which are brand new IP''s.\r\n\r\nHere''s a list of games confirmed to be in development for the Xbox One:\r\n\r\n\r\n    Call of Duty: Ghosts\r\n    FIFA 14\r\n    Forza Motorsport 5\r\n    NBA Live 14\r\n    Madden NFL 14\r\n    Quantum Break\r\n    UFC\r\n    Halo 5\r\n    Destiny\r\n    Assassin''s Creed IV: Black Flag\r\n    Watch Dogs\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Xbox One will be released worldwide later this year.\r\nI''ll keep this thread updated with all the news, trailers, pictures and such.\r\nKeep in mind that this event was Part 1 of the big reveal, and at E3 in a few weeks, Microsoft will reveal even more details about the Xbox One.\r\nIn the meantime I''ll try and gather as many confirmed facts on the Xbox One as i can, and post them here.', 2239, 9, '2013-05-21 18:25:44', 46, 'no', ':16:9:1:2:1:55', 'N/A', '2013-05-27 22:52:23', 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 340, ':1', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2240, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'It was just confirmed that playing used games on the Xbox One will require you to pay an extra fee as each game is now tied directly with Xbox Live accounts. This could also mean the console is always online. ', 2239, 16, '2013-05-21 18:27:52', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2241, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', '[quote pid=2240]\r\n\r\nActually it was confirmed a few weeks ago that the Xbox One will not be "Always Online".\r\n\r\nhttp://gamepolitics.com/2013/05/06/report-durango-designed-work-todays-internet#.UZu87UoqK80', 2239, 9, '2013-05-21 18:30:41', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2242, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'Hmmm, then I wonder how they will link the game to the Xbox Live account. Guess it just has to be connected for activation and thats it.\r\n\r\nRegardless, Sony stocks have risen 8.75% today, and the spike began at 1pm Eastern. Reaction so far on blogs, twitter, and comment sections have been... poor to say the least. \r\n\r\nI can''t claim to be unbiased in this as I''m pretty big on Sony, but this reveal was pretty lackluster. Microsoft has created an entertainment system, while Sony has created a video game console. As a video game fan, which do you think I liked more. (Hint: it''s the one that actually still allows for free use of used games.)', 2239, 16, '2013-05-21 18:54:37', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2243, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'I don''t think that because the new Xbox is more an entertainment system, than a video game console, it''s worse than the PS4. PC gamers use their computers for watching films, TV shows and listen to music as well, but that''s not a downside.\r\n\r\nThe Xbox One still plays games just fine, i don''t see the downside of being able to watch movies, or listen to music on it as well. I like the idea of having one machine that i can use for my gaming, movie and music needs.', 2239, 9, '2013-05-21 19:00:28', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2246, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'Can someone link me to the source for that pay to play used games thing?\r\n\r\nAbout Halo; they may be milking the franchise, but weren''t Reach and Halo 4 really really good games? Most people seemed to think so. And Forward Unto Dawn was fantastic in my opinion. Whats wrong with them milking their franchise, when we actually get good, solid and fun products from it?\r\n\r\nAbout the console; A lot of the criticisms i looked up seem to center on the "i already have a cable box" or something along the lines of it not being too gaming related.\r\nThe Xbox One plays next generation games, It has a lot of exclusives, some of which we have very high expectations for, and we think they''re going to be really good. Why can''t that same machine be allowed to let you listen to music, or watch TV? It already does what It''s supposed to be doing, quite well. Better than the current Xbox does, all the other stuff is just a bonus in my opinion.\r\n20 years ago, a phone was something you could call people with, or people could call you. Now a phone lets you send E Mails, take pictures and film events, and even game. I see the same evolution for all the consoles; they''re evolving to be more than they were before. What''s wrong with that?\r\n\r\n', 2239, 9, '2013-05-21 19:18:02', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2244, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', '[quote pid=2243]\r\n\r\nIm pretty sure that can be used on the PS3 as well...and PS4 will indeed allow you to do that. I just dont like the idea of paying a fee to play a used game. Now, if it was backwards compatible, and you had to pay a small fee to make it so, then I will agree to that. \r\n\r\nOne of the biggest things that irked me, was how bad they are milking Halo. As a long-time Halo Fan Boy, I must say I am weeping. Halo died once Bungie left...Microsoft is trying to milk the series dry for every last dollar. Glad i switched over to the PS3. And thinking about switching to the PS4. ', 2239, 34, '2013-05-21 19:09:49', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2245, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', '[quote pid=2243]\r\n\r\nMy PS3 does that right now. The Xbox 360 does that now. This isn''t innovation. This is adding bells and whistles to an industry standard and acting like you just invented it. Microsoft didn''t bring anything new to the table. \r\n\r\nWhat ultimately matters is the games, and how you play them. Microsoft went heavily into the casual market, and lead off with multiplatform games. Its obvious Microsoft wants a share of the casual market that Nintendo grabbed up with the Wii. But I see this turning out like the Wii U in a way. It will sell much much better than the Wii U, but I don''t see gamers, aside from the CoD/Halo crowd being that enthusiastic about it.\r\n\r\nNo, it isn''t a downside to have all that. But it isn''t an upside to see that focused on and shoved down our throats, like the Kinect, not to mention, current consoles do all that anyway. \r\n\r\nAs I''ve stated many many times, games are what sell me on what to buy. And with Microsoft putting so much emphasis on the bells and whistles, but not talking gaming innovation (COD HAS DOGS OMFG!) and Sony showcasing numerous innovative titles, I''m obviously gonna hate on the Xbox. Is it going to be a bad console? It certainly isn''t for me, thats all I can say. ', 2239, 16, '2013-05-21 19:17:10', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2247, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'http://www.computerandvideogames.com/407912/microsoft-confirms-pre-owned-fee-for-xbox-one/\r\n\r\n\r\nI''m very glad Microsoft is pushing for more exclusives, but they have to be quality exclusives. The 360 had a ton of exclusives that weren''t worth a damn. Like I said, I don''t care about the extra things. Its nice to have them, but will they make or break my buying of the system? Nope. The games will, and Microsoft didn''t show anything that wowed me or made me think I would need to buy the One.\r\n\r\nCompare that to Sony which brought numerous first and third party developers onto the stage. We saw Square Enix, Sucker Punch, Capcom, indie developers, among others. Sony also released a massive list of development teams for the PS4, and from looking at it, I can safely say at least half are working on exclusives.\r\n\r\nMicrosoft on the other hand had EA Sports, Microsoft Studios, and Infinity Ward. The track record for Microsoft has left a lot to be desired as a gamer who values games above all things. \r\n\r\nI wasn''t impressed in anyway by the Xbox One. While I wasn''t too impressed by the PS4 either, its obvious to me Sony is still in the business of making the words "video game" in video game console its priority. Everything in Sony''s conference revolved around the games, and what you could do. Half of Microsoft''s conference was dedicated to entertainment. \r\n\r\nSony has created a video game console, where video games are the focus. I think all the extra things are pointless. I can press one button and be back to watching TV. I can press another button and be listening to music. I can already do all that. The One didn''t show anything new. \r\n\r\nAs for always Online, certain games may require it, but not the console itself (not different from this generation). Also, no game purchases from the 360 will carry over to the One. And all that TV stuff they showed off, turns out its a [url=http://www.vg247.com/2013/05/21/xbox-one-live-tv-available-in-us-only-at-launch-requires-separate-device/]seperate device that will have to be purchased.[/url] The more that comes out, the more I find that I''m hating what Microsoft is doing. It also appears MS is using a slower RAM than what the PS4 will be doing, and the lack of technical details seems to be aiding rumors that the One is in fact, technically inferior to the PS4. \r\n', 2239, 16, '2013-05-21 19:46:49', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2248, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'I''m feeling pretty woozy right now, so I''ll post some more here tomorrow.\r\n\r\nFor now; I agree that Sony is focusing more on gaming, and that Microsoft needs to focus more on gaming. But i don''t think the Xbox One is anywhere near as bad and horrible as people are making it out to be, just because we didn''t get a lot of gaming related information on it today. E3 is coming up, and we can hope there''s better news to be had then.\r\n\r\nUPDATE: Here''s some collected info on the One (you have to admit, having to call a console "the One" is pretty awesome), along with some info on the used games policies: [url=http://gamepolitics.com/2013/05/21/microsoft-unveils-xbox-one#.UZvokkoqK80]Xbox One info[/url]', 2239, 9, '2013-05-21 20:55:31', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2249, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'No, calling a console The One is pretty silly sounding to be honest. \r\n\r\nAnd I see almost no one defending this console except the die hards. Microsofts stock has dropped, while Sony''s has increased around 10% at this point. It''s pretty much universal opinion that Microsoft failed in spectacular fashion in exciting people for this entertainment box. They delayed this conference a whole month to respond better to Sony and this is the steaming pile of shit they gave us. They would have been better served to simply wait until freaking E3 to show off the new console. \r\n\r\nThe Xbox One doesn''t seem like a next gen console. Its like Xbox 360 3.0. There is no innovation on it that relates to gaming what so ever. Everything the One does, has already been done. Meanwhile Sony adds a share button, makes indie development easier than ever before, DOESN''T CHARGE EXTRA TO PLAY USED GAMES, and as usual, shows off a much better library of GAMES!\r\n\r\nBecause thats what these are supposed to be. VIDEO GAME CONSOLES. Not a damn All in One PC! The hard core, blinded Xbox fans will of course upgrade, but this is going to turn out like the Wii U I bet (oh, which btw, launched with exclusives too.) They are selling this to the casual fan, but why the hell would a casual fan pay $499 for something they already freaking have with the Wii, 360, or PS3.\r\n\r\nWhat would it take for Microsoft to gain my support of this box? Drop the damn used game fee, show an interest in innovation, and for the love of god, dont make this a freaking fantasy sports machine. GO GET NEW GAME DEVELOPERS! I don''t give a rats ass that your new shooter has fish that actually move out of the way when you are swimming, or showcases graphics that have been surpassed 6 years ago. I want to see something new! Quantum Break is new, and they spent maybe 45 seconds on it but spent how long with EA Sports? How long with CoD Ghosts. How long talking about a damned TV!? \r\n\r\nThe PS4 feels like a brand new generation of gaming consoles. The Xbox One feels like a lazy re-branding of the 360. I honestly don''t see any reason what so ever for me to change my mind. The more the extra crap is brought up, the angrier I get. Because I am a gamer, and I want gaming innovation. Not gaming stagnation. This was Microsofts time to shine, and instead they are now dodging questions about a crappy used game policy, and playing up a Halo TV series (which was announced a console unveiling? wut?) They blew it. \r\n\r\n\r\nBIG EDIT: Microsoft says the console has to be online at least ONCE PER DAY. Might as well be always online.', 2239, 16, '2013-05-21 22:42:37', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2250, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'http://wegotthiscovered.com/gaming/xbox-one-always-online-gamerscore-backwards-compatible/\r\n\r\nThat "always online" thing really doesn''t seem that bad at this point. It really doesn''t sound like it will totally cripple the console.\r\n\r\nAnd i don''t get why you seem so upset about this whole thing Bats, Sony just went in one direction while Microsoft went in another. Sony is focusing on gaming first and foremost, while Microsoft is aiming for a much wider audience. \r\nBut from what i understand, the Xbox One will still do the most important thing with It''s games: It will bring Xbox users 8th Generation games. Not a whole lot more at this point, but it will do that at least. Sony will bring it''s users 8th Generation gaming and more, but not a whole lot else.\r\n\r\nAt this point, Sony has it''s gaming innovations and focus going for them, and It will probably appeal mainly to the core or hardcore gamer fanbases. Microsoft has gaming, TV, Music and some other stuff going for them, and they may have bit off more than they can chew, but only time will tell. As it stands right now, I''m in favor of the One; It gives me the chance to play 8th Generation games, and that''s all i want. Sony is sticking to the formula that has worked for decades, but the way i see it Microsoft is exploring what else a single console can do.\r\n\r\nWhat happens if at E3 Sony just shows more games? Just more of all things gaming related? If all you ever wanted from a console is games, and nothing more that''s your console. \r\nMicrosoft will show a lot of new things at E3, including new games, and all the extra stuff as well. Xbox One is just exploring a wider consumer base, while possible losing some in the gaming community.\r\n\r\nTo sum up my stance; Sony is staying true to the old formula, Games first. I have no problem with it, and I am very much still on the fence about which console to invest in.\r\nMicrosoft is trying new things, focusing less on some areas and trying to win more in others, and I don''t see anything wrong with that.\r\n\r\nWhy shouldn''t our gaming consoles try to evolve beyond a single task?', 2239, 9, '2013-05-21 23:23:41', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2251, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'That "always online" thing really is a bad idea...yes, the console doesnt always have to be online, but for once a day, it has to be. So, what will happen if it isn''t on? We don''t know...and that worrys me. Microsoft must know the gaming communities hatred for things that are "always online." So revealing that a check will happen once-a-day, without explaining it any further, really hindered their progress of gaining support from the gaming community. \r\n\r\nSo what will happen when I lose my connection due to a network difficulty, and the check happens at that point? Will I get penalized? So far, we dont know, and that fact is making people worried. If there is any sort of penalization, then Microsoft shall lose a lot of customers, and their image will plunge. \r\n\r\nNow, I understand what Microsoft is planning to do with this console...they want to make it an all entertainment system. Is this wrong? No. They can put whatever they want out into the market. Now, what i do not agree with them, is their claim of innovation. I hardly see anything that is a major innovative experience. While watching the live press release, I heard and saw nothing but bells and whistles. The xbox 360 and PS3 can do all that...you can watch movies, go to FB, listen to music, and play games. As Solidbatman said, Xbox One is just Xbox 360 2.0.\r\n\r\nNow, you say they are innovating the console like the phone, to not make it into only a Video Game console, but a full entertainment one. But...if a phone cannot do the basic service of making a phone call reliably, then it doesnt matter what else it has. If Microsoft doesn''t make that portion work, then they failed at making the next generation console. Now, imagine this, on a Console release conference, they spent half of it, talking about the ability to watch TV, which you need another device for! Which they failed to mention! They also spent a quarter of it, talking about CoD: GHOSTS. A game released on most consoles...really? Just say that the Xbox One will have exclusive DLC content, and that is it...dont spend that much time talking about a game that isnt an exclusive. \r\n\r\nPaying a "small" fee to play used games? How small is small? Now, what about their fees to go to Xbox Live? Their fees to use their exclusive live streaming for sports? I had the Xbox 360 from the first year it came out till the beginning of August of 2012...and I must say, their Microsoft Points are not cheap, nor is Xbox Live. \r\n\r\n" Why shouldn''t our gaming consoles try to evolve beyond a single task?" -Absalon\r\n\r\nSony is trying to do that as well. Now, for the PS4, you have the ability to watch videos, listen to music and social network. Same thing what the Xbox One will do, but...with a few other bells and whistles. \r\n\r\nBut, I must say, it is still a bit early to be trashing Xbox One to the full extent of our abilities...we must wait till E3 for more information about the console. But for what we have been shown so far, it is an utter failure in the world of gaming. PS4 release conference gave us enough info to say that, Sony, has indeed brought a next generation console. ', 2239, 34, '2013-05-22 01:22:11', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2252, 'The Four Swords of Triumph', '[size=4][color=black]The Four Swords of Triumph[/color][/size]\r\n\r\n[b]-- Rules --[/b]\r\n1. If a player discovers a sword first, you are not allowed to steal it from them. This will banish you from the contest and you will lose the sword.\r\n\r\n2. You are allowed to challenge the wielder of the sword to combat. If you win, you get the sword. They have a right to accept or deny your combat request. If they deny it, perhaps appeasing them first would work (e.g., deals, trading, etc).\r\n\r\n3. Hints will be given for each sword''s location, but they will be subtle and no more hints shall be given than that.\r\n\r\n4. Whoever finds the sword, gets to keep the sword. It''s more of a "who-saw-it-first" kind of deal. If a problem with this arises, then the would-be wielders will duke it out with the weaponry that they have readily available. The winner will take the sword.\r\n\r\n5. Should you find a sword, using it for griefing with it will be [i]unacceptable[/i] and will land you a spot on the blacklist. \r\n\r\nThat''s pretty much it for the rules. Now on to the good stuff:\r\n\r\n[b]DIABLO[/b] - A sword made in Hell, and hidden in the Nether. Wields the power of fire (set enemies on fire [left click] and shoot fireballs [right click]).\r\n\r\nHint:\r\nThe sword of Hell hidden in sand\r\nA soulless dirt in no-man''s land\r\n\r\n[b]ENDER[/b] - A sword forged from the skin of the Ender Dragon, and hidden in The End. Wields the power of teleportation (move 10 blocks at a time [right click]).\r\n\r\nHint:\r\nIn the land of the dragon''s stare\r\nIs an uncovered chest with a sword quite rare\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]GLACIUS[/b] - A sword created by Frost Giants, stored deep in an icy ocean. Wields the power of ice (shoots blocks of ice [right click]).\r\n\r\nHint:\r\nThe power of ice in a frozen land\r\nYou wield the Frost Giant in your hand\r\nLaying deep under the frozen water\r\nThank God you haven''t fought her\r\n\r\n[b]THOR[/b] - A sword, truly great and powerful, forged from the remnants of Mjolnir. Wields the power of thunder and lightning (10% chance to strike foes with lightning [left click], send a rumble of thunder to an enemy and launch them in the air [right click]).\r\n\r\nHint:\r\nDeep in the jungle, a circle of wither\r\nA treetop of ice whispers, "come hither"\r\n\r\n\r\nThese swords will be hidden tonight and the contest will start on Friday, [b]May 24th[/b] at 10 A.M. EST. You may only use them on the survival map, and they may not be taken anywhere else (you also may not acquire them using cheats). I haven''t come up with anything special for having all four swords yet, but when I do, I''ll post something about it. Remember, play fair everyone, and may the best warrior win.\r\n\r\nGame On!', 2252, 1, '2013-05-22 02:19:14', 46, 'no', ':1:34:2:1:55', 'Hidden in various locations!', '2013-05-24 16:03:51', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 135, '', '', 'no', 'minecraft, contest, sword, four, triumph, diablo, thor, glacius, ender', 'Added hints.', ''),
(2265, 'Re: Update: The Four Swords Contest', 'I''ve also added a 200G achievement for each sword found, but I can''t give them to you if I don''t know that you''ve found them. So please be sure to post when/if you find one.', 2263, 1, '2013-05-24 16:16:51', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2253, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', '[img]http://www.southbayriders.com/forums/attachments/412649/[/img]\n\nWell, one thing we can all agree on is this: [i]at least they''re not Nintendo[/i]. They''re claiming all Let''s Play YouTubers'' videos and making money off of them from the ads, and let''s face it, the Wii U suuuucks.', 2239, 1, '2013-05-22 04:37:55', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
(2254, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'I actively try not to defer my opinions or beliefs to someone else, but Tim Buckley, author of the web comic Ctrl+Alt+Del just released a newspost on his site that conveys my side of this argument a lot better than i think I''d be able to.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.cad-comic.com/\r\n\r\nIt''s a good read, and It''s a nice break from the massive hate storm the X1 (we can call it that too, if you don''t like The One) has been getting.\r\nI can''t really think of more ways to present my side of the argument that wouldn''t just repeat what Tim says.\r\nAlso the comics are great fun, both of the ones up today are about the consoles reveals.', 2239, 9, '2013-05-22 15:30:29', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2255, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KbWgUO-Rqcw&feature=youtu.be\r\n\r\ntvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvtvdogscallofduty\r\n\r\nThis is why I''m so damn mad. This is the direction of the gaming industry. I want the Xbox One to fail so bad so no company even thinks of placing bells and whistles first again. Focus on the games, or I, and many other gamers will just no longer give a damn. \r\n\r\nSo sure, if you want to pay for a bunch of useless extra crap, go for it. I''ll be sitting here actually playing games that are worthwile just like I always have. Enjoy your sports and Call of Duty!', 2239, 16, '2013-05-22 16:43:02', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2256, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', '[quote pid=2255]\r\n\r\nYou could do that with just about anything.\r\n\r\nAnd what are you so mad about? You don''t like what X1 offers, nobody is forcing you to get one. \r\n\r\nTo reiterate mine and Tim Buckleys point; The gaming aspect of the X1 and PS4 are a given. Of course they''re going to have games, and of course those games are going to be next generation. They are still gaming consoles.\r\nWhat Sony did in their presentation was focus on what gaming is like on the PS4, what Microsoft did is show what [i]else[/i] the next generation of consoles can do. It''s two different focus areas, but they are still more or less the same.\r\n\r\nThink about it, E3 is in a few weeks, so why would Microsoft show all the gaming related stuff first, when It''s already a given that they have it? Wouldn''t it make more sense to get into the gaming details at [i]the[/i] gaming convention? \r\nOf course Microsoft will show us more games, and what else the console is capable of, but why hate them so intently just because they want to show us that a console do other stuff too? It''s been a day since the announcement, and people are already calling the TV related stuff a deal breaker, without even having seen Microsofts full menu?\r\n\r\nGamers are saying any of the following is deal breakers; fee for used games, too much TV, not enough games and all such things. But are they forgetting that consoles grow and adapt during their lifetime? Look at the Xbox 360 when it first launched, and look at what it is now. It''s actually very different, it offers more of everything instead of staying focused on a single thing. Both Microsoft and Sony will adapt their consoles according to feedback, It''s not like everything Microsoft or Sony says is already set in stone, the fee to play used games, the sometimes online thing, all of that can change according to what their consumers want from them, yet gamers are swearing off everything Microsoft has offered in one day. \r\n\r\nI''m kind of sad that so many gamers appear so shortsighted, only focusing so harshly and negatively on what was said in the course of a single day, instead of just cutting back, and letting Microsoft present their full ideas.', 2239, 9, '2013-05-22 17:06:40', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2257, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'Guys, jeez, come on, it''s a damn gaming console. Chill. If you don''t like it, don''t buy it. There''s nothing wrong with a debate but put your personal feelings aside. Let''s just tone it down a bit guys.', 2239, 1, '2013-05-22 21:08:24', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2258, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'No, what I''m upset about is that the focus seems to be getting lost in glitter and crayons. Microsoft really focused on the casual audience, while ignoring the core of their audience. I understand E3 is coming up, so I''m also upset on how poorly Microsoft chose to date this conference. I''m also upset because Microsoft delayed their conference a month and this is what we got. I was expecting them to come out swinging, aiming for the top again, and trying to outdo Sony. Instead, I got to watch them talk about watching TV through an Xbox instead of... well... my tv.\r\n\r\nSo I''m furious, because I see gaming consoles becoming irrelevant as a gaming console. This is the beginning of the pandering. It''s fine to try and gain a new audience, but I felt like Microsoft ignored the gaming audience. \r\n\r\nLook, it may not matter to you guys because you guys don''t play the same style of games I play. You guys want functionality, you guys want glitter and extra stuff. Thats fine, but people like me were ignored by Microsoft. People like me wanted to see a step forward in terms of gaming, not in terms of living room family entertainment. I wanted to see Microsoft step out and show an interest in the rest of the world. All those cool things will only be available to the US. No, Europe or Japan are not getting HBO, ESPN, or anything like that now. The entire conference was US driven. It ignored the rest of the world. \r\n\r\nE3 may really change my mind, and I may eat every last one of my words if Microsoft comes out swinging and charging headfirst into a sea of innovative, third party exclusives. But based on the track record, and the focus of the latest conference, I find it hard to believe that Microsoft is going to really do this. I feel like we''ll see the same thing we always see. Sports, Call of Duty, Kinect, and some random, non gaming feature (Xbox TV in this case). \r\n\r\nSo I''m mad because I expected so much more from them. I''m mad because I see a terrible trend taking place. I''m mad because as a gamer, I felt ignored. I''m overreacting I''m sure, but gaming is my number one past time. I would love to become a gaming journalist. I know most gaming related news before 99% of my friends. I try to keep up with every genre out there, even the ones I don''t care about personally. I''m extremely passionate about games. I spend most of my income on them after bills and living expenses. I try everything in my power to get people to try new games and genres. This isn''t just games for me. This is pretty much my lifestyle. And I feel like Microsoft just pissed all over it.\r\n\r\nI apologize for my angry rants, but this is very important to me, gaming comes first to me. I don''t want to see a second industry crash, but signs are pointing towards it happening, and I see similarities to the 1983 crash. Xbox One may turn out to be an incredible system, but I saw nothing that gave me any hope for it. If you remember, I was disappointed by the PS4, but reserved most of my judgement. I jumped the gun on this and let my bias show. I should have reserved  judgment until E3, but I was too angry about the direction I saw Microsoft go. \r\n\r\n\r\nThere we go, civility restored. ', 2239, 16, '2013-05-23 02:42:31', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2259, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'Lol good and you do make very, very good points, as usual. That''s why I don''t join debates cause I always get too angry in em haha. :P', 2239, 1, '2013-05-23 02:46:29', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2260, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'Gonna try and ease the tension here with some Gaming information for the X1:\r\n\r\nThe Achievement system is getting upgraded, so that your achievements doesn''t just count for a single game, but across all your games. The post with this info also claims that there will be several ways to earn achievements, and that the records will indicate not just which achievements you earned, but also how.\r\n\r\n[img]http://compass.xboxlive.com/assets/0e/9c/0e9cb15b-c8ed-44a6-b977-de7566805447.jpg?n=XBR_Image31.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\nThey also mention something called Living Games technology. This will sync your game stats with real world stats, and allow for a more realistic and engaging experience. But they only mention this for Sports games, so I don''t know if it''ll include other genres at launch, but it does have some potential.\r\n\r\nAlso new is what they call the Smart Match system. I gather it''s just fancy talk for improved match making, but It''s a welcome update.\r\n\r\nAnd finally, the X1 will have an in game recorder, available for all games it seems. This feature has been specifically requested/hoped for by Youtubers who run gaming channels. It could also be a useful tool for sites like ours.', 2239, 9, '2013-05-23 14:31:37', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2261, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'I have to say, I really do love the DVR thing. Not sure how I feel about the achievements, though.', 2239, 1, '2013-05-23 18:01:04', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2262, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'I can''t remember if i mentioned it, but your current Gamerscore will be transferred to the X1.\r\n\r\nEDIT:\r\n\r\nI think I''d like to offer my criticisms of the X1, now that I''ve had some time to digest it all.\r\n\r\nNote that i am no where near as hateful or disappointed as the rest of the internet is. It''s far, far too early to hate the X1 or Microsoft for anything they''ve announced.\r\n\r\nThat being said, my concerns are about the following:\r\n\r\n1. The TV stuffs. I am not against having my Xbox working as my cable box as well as my gaming console. But, a lot of what Microsoft has announced at previous E3''s has almost always been aimed mainly at, or been exclusive to the US, and not even all of the US, Hawaii just gets no love. And as a European, I really hate the fact that Microsoft time and time again don''t do enough to encourage the markets outside the continental US.\r\nIf they give me the option to use the TV functions, I would take it. But If it''s just something that only certain parts of the US can use, I''ll be pretty fucking disappointed.\r\nAlso, the rumors that suggest you still have to have a cable box for it to work are downright stupid. Doesn''t that negate having that function in the Xbox completely? \r\n\r\n2. The Kinect. The voice commands are cool, and if they work as well as demonstrated this time around, I might even actually use them. \r\n"Xbox on", "Xbox watch TV", It''s nice and simple. Hell I''d say downright calming. No more searching for a remote or fiddling with the buttons, It''s a simple mechanic, and if it works, Fuck Right, well done.\r\nBut, I do not want my Xbox to be totally dependent on that device being connected. For practical reasons not everyone may have the required space for it to stand in a reasonable position, not everyone wants to use any of It''s functions, and they shouldn''t be forced to use it. \r\n\r\nTo summarize; I want the TV extras to work on an as global as possible scale, and not just the US. And I want less Kinect dependency.\r\n\r\nI am actually OK with the used games fee. I can see how it makes sense, lemme explain.\r\nYou go and buy a new game, and as the X1 requires you to install it onto your harddrive, you don''t need the disc after that. Now, people get upset here because they can''t simply "lend" that game to a friend for them to play, but with the X1, you aren''t really lending that game out; It''s linked to your account, It''s installed to your Xbox. Technically speaking you still possess that game. Your friends do not. They have not paid for the game you have just given them to play. I can see the logic in that, seeing as you never really forfeit the game you own, and whoever borrows it haven''t bought the rights to play it in the first place, I can see why there would be a fee. It''s like an upgraded new games policy.\r\nGranted I don''t usually buy used games, in fact off the top of my head i can recall 2 used games i own. But i know, and fully understand that a lot of gamers operate on a budget, that might not allow them to always pay full price for a new title. Buut, according to Gamestop and Microsoft you will still be able to trade in your games at retailers, so there''s hope yet.', 2239, 9, '2013-05-23 20:02:25', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
