(2271, 'Re: Xbox Reveal', 'Interestingly enough, I also don''t have much issue with the used game policy in the short term. However, long term, I have major major reservations.\r\n\r\nIn the short term, I have no problem with it because I''d love to see good developers get rewarded for good work. I think it''s a shame Gamestop can take off $5, call a game used, and get 100% return on the game while the developer gets nothing. However, after a year or so, I have no problem with Gamestop making money off used games. \r\n\r\nNow here is where my issues begin. 5 years from now, I might want a certain game to add to my collection and play. Am I still going to be required to pay an extra fee (if thats what Microsoft decided to go with, they have been very unclear and contradictory on the issue). Or, will Microsoft waive any sort of fee after a certain amount of time? \r\n\r\nIf I get an Xbox One down the road, I doubt I will care about collecting games for it if there is any sort of used game fee. Because more often than not, you can''t tell whats worth collecting and what isn''t. \r\n', 2239, 16, '2013-05-27 22:52:23', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
