(2282, 'A Really Big Change', 'Hey guys, it''s been a while. Yesterday I got to thinking something: we''re pretty big on Minecraft. Almost all of us are on there on the server, and those of us that aren''t, simply lack the capabilities of getting on (I wont call out any names [solidbatman], don''t worry). But anyway, (and think before you blurt out at me in rage or what-have-you), what would you think about turning DreamSpand into a Minecraft-site? I could redo the boards and everything, and I could make a sub-board to store all of our current topics and posts so that they don''t get lost forever. I''m working on an example on my computer and I figure content will be much, MUCH easier to work on that way because it will be all Minecraft/Tekkit/FTB/Big Dig/Big Reactors/Voltz/etc. I think our main problem, which is something that you guys have said before, is that we''re too generalized. I understand things taking a while to get started sometimes, but it''s been over a year. It''s time to do something different. I would redo the homepage and everything...again...but that''s okay, it will be much easier to implement things if it''s based off of one subject. And there again, sites based off of one particular subject are my specialty, it''s why my last sites flourished so well. And the best part about that, is that they were built and themed around something called chao, which have admittedly been dead for at least 10 or so years, yet they still had over two thousand members each. One of them, the one I made from scratch, had over 5,000 at one point, in just a couple of years. I had managed to reach 100 members before six months even came, and 1,000 members within a year.\r\n\r\nSo if we make this site about something that''s still very much alive, it will be twice that. We''ll have a much bigger and better purpose, and I do believe things will be a heck of a lot easier. I''ve talked with Michael about it and he said it sounded good, but I''m not one to just suddenly make a change without telling you guys about it first. I want to hear your thoughts, so tell me what you think: if you''re for it or against it, what kind of changes you think we''d need to make or what changes NOT to make, etc. I''ve already got a new skin made on my computer that I''m still working on. And imagine the modders that would bring stuff here - we could be the home site for the next big mod. There''s so many possibilities, and it really wouldn''t be that difficult to do. I mean, think about it, the site''s dead as a doornail. It has been for a while. We''re lucky if we get three people on in a day. Let''s put it out of its misery so something new can be born. The name will still be DreamSpand, though, so don''t worry about that. Discuss!', 2282, 1, '2013-06-18 14:46:43', 46, 'no', ':1:16:34:2:9:46:14:1:5:55:32', 'What would you say about turning the site into a Minecraft site?', '2013-06-20 00:26:43', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 150, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2283, 'Re: A Really Big Change', 'inb4 9 year olds join. \r\n\r\nThe only thing you have to consider with that is server capacity. If it takes off like you hope, you''re looking at much larger expenses for the MC server as well as a lot more plug in work to prevent griefers.\r\n\r\nMy opinion is neutral. I have a new audience and location for my writings, so if you guys go MC forum, thats fine with me.', 2282, 16, '2013-06-18 20:15:12', 46, 'yes', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
