(2288, 'Update: Gone Minecraft!', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]Attention everyone: DreamSpand has gone Minecraft!\n\nYes, that''s right, we are now a Minecraft site. We believed that the site needed more direction, and Minecraft seemed the be the right direction to go, what with the server and how much the majority of us know about the game and its add-ons. Soon the site homepage will be Minecraft-oriented, as well. The games and pages have been removed from the site so that new, fresh content could be added. A tutorial for basic Minecraft stuff will be up shortly. Any of the staff can begin work on any of the pages as they see fit. Comments [i]will[/i] be enabled on these content pages unless specified otherwise.\n\nThe forums have received the biggest Minecraft-themed treatment, with new boards and categories completely redesigned and old, DreamSpand v1.0 topics have been moved to the "Vault" board. More changes will be coming soon, so be expecting those. Hope you come to enjoy the changes.[br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 2288, 3, '2013-06-20 19:09:27', 28, 'no', ':1:2:16:1:2:55:2', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 53, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2289, 'Submission Guidelines', 'Please be sure that you follow these guidelines before submitting your mod into our database:\n\n1. Make sure it works, preferably with the current version of Minecraft. If it does not work with the current build, specify what version it [i]does[/i] work with.\n\n2. This is not a place for plugins. We have a Plugins board, just post it there.\n\n3. Do not post any offensive or harmful mods. This will get you banned.\n\n4. Give a detailed description of your mod, and be sure to add screenshots. We won''t accept your mod if you don''t provide a screenshot of what it does in-game.\n\n5. Make sure it hasn''t been submitted before. You can submit mods willy-nilly, but if you submit a mod that does the same exact thing as another mod, then we won''t accept it because that''s just redundant.\n\n6. Don''t be bummed out if your mod doesn''t make it to our database. It''s still in the submission area and people will still see it, so it''s not the end of the world.\n\n7. Don''t be a jerk in the description - be warm and inviting. Otherwise people aren''t going to trust you or your mod.\n\n8. Be sure to provide [b]ALL[/b] necessary items for your mod. Don''t leave anything out.\n\n9. If someone asks for help or something they''re confused about, answer them. The way you respond to other users will also be checked, if one should respond.\n\n10. The mod must be yours. You must be the creator of it as it is plagiarism otherwise.', 2289, 1, '2013-06-21 17:24:46', 57, 'no', ':1:9:1:16:5:55', 'Follow these!', '2013-06-21 17:24:46', 0, 1, 1, 0, 1, 239, '', '', 'no', 'submission, guidelines, minecraft, mod, submit, database, dev', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
