(2433, 'Update: AlphaPack Server (Replacing Tekkit)', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]Hey folks! Sorry about the issues with Tekkit during the past few days. The technic launcher released a build for 1.6.4, but it was very unstable. We spent days trying to upgrade it, and even tech support failed. Actually, they made it worse. So I went in and did something different, that I spent all day doing today. First of all, some of you know that I''ve been modding Minecraft for a few months now. I have four of my own mods added on to this new server, the [b]AlphaPack Server[/b]. It''s my very first mod pack. However, it''s not just my mods. There are [i]many other[/i] mods added on to it, including (but not limited to) GalactiCraft, ComputerCraft, Twilight Forest, Modular PowerSuits, MineFactory-Reloaded, MystCraft, BuildCraft, and many, many more.\n\nNote: This is not Tekkit. It is regular 1.6.4 Minecraft with the 1.6.4 version of Forge.\n\nYou can download the full AlphaPack mod pack here: http://www.dreamspand.com/mods/AlphaPack.zip\n\n[b]Part One - Mod Files[/b]\n1.) Extract the zip file\n2.) Take all of the mods out of the "mods" folder in the zip file\n3.) Put them inside your mods folder in %appdata% -> .minecraft -> mods\n4.) Done!\n\n** Install these mods in your "mods" folder in your .minecraft folder under AppData. \n\nAlso, download this one as well:\nhttp://www.dreamspand.com/config.zip\n\nDue to compatibility issues, some IDs were changed to allow them to work together. This means that you need to replace the config files with the newly changed IDs.\n\n[b]Part Two - Config Files[/b]\n1.) Extract the zip file\n2.) Copy the "config" folder to %appdata% -> .minecraft\n3.) This should replace the necessary files\n4.) Done!\n\n** Replace your "config" folder with this after unzipping it or you may have ID errors.\n\nIf you need further assistance, please, don''t hesitate to post about it or message a staff member. We''ll get back to you as soon as we can, either way, and we''ll be happy to help. Once all of the mods are installed, you can join the server.\n\nThe IP for the AlphaPack Server is: 192.227.248.110:47407\n\nPaste that in the Server IP portion when you click on Add Server. \n\nAlso, the Tekkit worlds are not "gone", they''ve just been decommissioned temporarily. However, we did purchase a new server host today, or rather Mike did. We have twice the gigs and half the price. We''re still setting it up, but that''s where our Tekkit worlds went. We''re working very diligently. While we get this setup, please feel free to check out the AlphaPack Server. There are a lot of mods, and a lot of things to do. We hope to see you around![br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 2433, 3, '2014-01-19 00:18:30', 28, 'no', ':1:2:5:2', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 48, '', '', 'no', '', '[Quick-Edit]', ''),
