(2483, 'Fluix Energized items How to - Asyl', 'These items are powered by RF, or Redstone Flux, is the only energy it will take.\r\nThe reason why i post this on Machinery is because you will need the following Machines and enough production of energy just to even keep these items full with energy. I currently have the Fluix Sword and the Fluix Pick both are pretty costly to make. \r\n\r\n\r\nFor this Tutorial you will need\r\n[list]\r\n[*]Redstone (about 3 stacks)\r\n[*]Diamonds (38 )\r\n[*]Blaze powder (64)\r\n[*]Pulverized obsidian (64)\r\n[*]Induction Smelter (1)\r\n[*]Energetic Infuser (depends how much power you have running through your circuit)\r\n[*] Pulverized Coal\r\n[*]Sulfur (not the block!)\r\n[/list]\r\n[color=fff000]*OPTIONAL* [/color] GLOWSTONE \r\n\r\n[color=000000]If you have [color=ff0000]Blaze Powder[/color] then skip this part![/color]\r\n\r\nOK first things first If you don''t have any Blaze powders then that is easy to fix. \r\nif you DO NOT have any Blaze Powder first thing you will need to do is put the Magma crucible and the Fluid Transposer Together and have the Fluid go in automatically using the Configuration option once the two machines are placed together.\r\n\r\nplace in a stack of Rdstone in the crucible. Now you will notice that the redstone is depleting and the little bar on the right is not gathering any redstone. well thats because you have it set to go into the transposer. If you check the transposer there you will see that the redstone is filling up the bar there. \r\n\r\nThe redstone there is now called Destabilized redstone. \r\n\r\nNow that you have destabilized redstone place a stack of glowstone and there you will start gaining some Blaze Powder. \r\n\r\nThat is how you make some Blaze powder.\r\n\r\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nWe need some Pyrotheum dust to make it \r\n\r\nplace the coal, blaze powder, sulfur, and redstone into a crafting table.\r\nTADAA! Pyrotheum dust.\r\n\r\nNow make a good 30 of it keep those in your inventory as we will need them later!\r\n\r\nnow do you remember on how to make the elecrtum blend? well make em! if not \r\nPulverized gold and pulverized silver\r\n\r\nnow that you have some electrum place those suckers in the Fluid Transposer and you will start noticing its making something well thats the Fluxed Electrum blend.\r\n\r\nnow for Each 2 Pyrotheum dust and 1 Fluxed Electrum Blend it will make the Fluxed Ingot.\r\n\r\n---------------------CONGRATZ for your first Fluxed Ingot!-------------------\r\n\r\nwe aren''t finished yet!\r\n\r\nwe need to make some obisidian rods to make the tools!\r\n\r\nfor this part you will need:\r\npulverized obsidian and blaze powder.\r\nnow this recipee isnt shapeless so you will need on pulverized obisidian on 2 ends. on on the top right and one on the bottom left, and place a blaze rod in between.\r\n\r\nwe arent done yet though!\r\n\r\nwe need some fluxed Crystals too!\r\n\r\njust do the same thing with the diamonds as we did to the Electrum and the Glowstone.\r\n\r\nand out will pop out some Fluxed Crystals. \r\n\r\nnow repeat the recipe for the Obisidian rods but this time instead of the pulverized obsidian, place the Fluxed Crystal.\r\nReplace the Blaze powder with the Obisidian Rod.\r\n\r\nyou will make the Infused Obsidian Rod. \r\n\r\nnow craft the tools you want to make by using the Flux ingots and the Infused Obsidian Rod.\r\n\r\nto power them up you must first fill it up with energy. That is where we will need the Energetic Infuser. The energetic Infuser will charge the tool. \r\n\r\nonce the tool is fully charged Pres "V" once you have your tool in hand, and watch it activate! :D\r\n\r\n                          congratulations you have made your first Flux Tool!\r\n\r\n+ Rep if this Tutorial has helped you!', 2483, 5, '2014-03-05 19:13:15', 62, 'no', ':5:2:1', 'N/A', '2014-03-05 19:13:15', 