(2501, 'About DreamCraft', '[size=6]DreamCraft[/size]\r\n\r\nDreamCraft is a server that has been around since March 17th of 2013, and it''s been built on a lot. The main spawn area is in the world simply called [b]survival[/b], and you spawn in a town-like area. In this area are multiple shops:\r\n\r\n[b]Flower Shop[/b]\r\nA pink building off to the side of the starter villages. You can buy or sell any type of flower here.\r\n\r\n[b]Farmer''s Market[/b]\r\nA building made of hay that''s up pretty high, anything and everything farm-related goes there. This includes fish and tree saplings. You can even buy and sell flowers and seeds there. A great way to make money is to work on your own farm, then sell some of it to make a quick buck. The prices are also relatively cheap, in case you need a certain crop that you''re having trouble finding.\r\n\r\n[b]General Shop[/b]\r\nThis shop is a black building made up of coal blocks. You can buy and sell misc things here, including but not limited to diamonds, iron ingots, emeralds, gold, redstone, slime balls, gunpowder, string, and cooked food. \r\n\r\n[b]Hardware Store[/b]\r\nThis building, made of blue stained clay, is where you may buy any kind of tool, such as axes, pickaxes, shovels and hoes. You can also buy and sell clocks, compasses, flint and steel, empty maps and fishing rods.\r\n\r\n[b]Bakery[/b]\r\nA building made up of brown stained clay. You can buy anything baking-related, such as bread, flour, sugar and cake.\r\n\r\n[b]Fishing Hole[/b]\r\nA small fishing hut made of wooden planks. You can not only buy and sell fish here, but it has a dock where you may fish at. A new addition is the fisherman''s Hall of Fame. Catch a decent amount of fish and/or show us your high fishing skill and you could have your character''s mugshot put there.\r\n\r\n[b]Minerail Shop[/b]\r\nPretty self-explanatory, you can buy anything related to minecarts and minecart rails here. Very expensive.\r\n\r\n[b]Armory[/b]\r\nHere you can buy weaponry and armor, both for yourself and for your horse(s). \r\n\r\n[b]Brewery[/b]\r\nAn upside-down half-sphere, you can buy any brewery ingredient here, as well as cauldrons and brewing stands. Just watch out for Hazel, the shopkeeper; she''s not a people person.\r\n\r\n[b]Archery Practice[/b]\r\nHere you can practice your archery. Imagine that. You can also buy a bow and/or arrows. Each color of wool is worth another set of points. We have no plugin integrated for this yet, so you''ll have to keep score for yourself. Still, it''s a great way to improve your shooting.\r\n\r\n[b]Library[/b]\r\nYou can buy and sell books and paper. We just can''t sell the enchanted books, because 1.) that would just make things too easy and 2.) the way the shop works does not allow us to.\r\n\r\n[b]Bank[/b]\r\nDefinitely one of the most useful (and fancy) buildings, this is where you can deposit and/or withdraw in-game money or xp. Money (in-game) and xp that you store in the bank will accumulate interest every so often, thereby increasing your funds. You can also check the balance of either one of them. Inside, there is a sign that you can right click called "Chatinteract", and it will let you manually decide what to do with your account via the chat. Type "quit" when you''re done with this mode. It also has a "drive-through" section on the side of the building, for quick access.\r\n\r\n[b]Headegg Shop[/b]\r\nThis building may seem a little strange. You can buy and sell [i]certain[/i] mob heads here. You also may buy or sell any type of spawn egg. Note, however, that not every spawn egg can be bought, and not every spawn egg can be sold. Things would get out of hand really quickly if we allowed people to buy Creepers and Wither Skeletons, let''s face it, folks.\r\n\r\n[b]Portals[/b]\r\nIn the back of the spawn point are MV portals that will take you to the designated biome on their signs, VERY far away. This is to allow players to build far and wide, instead of everyone living right close to each other. More portals will be added, but this way less resources are used up, and much less quickly. It provides an easy, efficient way for users to spread themselves apart.\r\n\r\n[b]TP Blocks[/b]\r\nThere is a section near the exit of Spawn made up of purple stained clay, and in this section, you will find numerous command blocks, preset with the teleportation command and the coordinates of peoples'' homes. This allows whoever wants one of these blocks, to tp to their home instantly, without the need of OP assistance. If you would like your own TP Block, please ask a staff member on the site or OP on the server, and we will be more than happy to add one for you. NOTE, however, that if this system is abused, the abuser will be kicked permanently from the server. Don''t harass or stalk people. Don''t go into their homes without their permission or follow them without their knowledge. That is not okay. You are free to go to and from your own home at your leisure, however, so long as you''re not spamming it. Also, if you should ask for a TP Block, you may also have one installed in your home, as a quick-access tp back to Spawn. \r\n\r\nThe Spawn point isn''t the only feature of the server, though it may be our most prominent. In the future, we intend to have multiple Spawn locations, and give each of them names. We also have plugins, one of them developed by yours truly, called BetaUtilities (though in the game it will simply say "beta" for now). This system allows players to set and use warps at their leisure. Again, so long as this system is not abused, it is free and open to all players.\r\n\r\n[b]Usage: [/b]\r\n/setwarp <warpName> - Allows you to set the specified warp. If this warp is previously set, it will overwrite the previous warp''s coordinates with the new one''s, rather than setting a new warp.\r\n\r\n/warp <warpName> - Warps the Player to the specified warp.\r\n\r\n/listwarps - Lists all available warps.\r\n\r\n[OP-Only]\r\n/delwarp <warpName> - Deletes the specified warp from the list.\r\n\r\n[size=4][b]Fun-Facts of DreamCraft Server[/b][/size]\r\n* When Creepers explode, they don''t damage the terrain - only Players. So no more losing your house.\r\n\r\n* When Players die, they do not lose their inventory. They will respawn with all of their items and their XP.\r\n\r\n* There are two other worlds, creative and kingdom. Only the first is open right now and can be reached from the TP Room. Each world and game-mode has its own separate inventory for each Player. This makes it easier to travel less confusingly from one world to the next, or previous, depending on your outlook of things.\r\n\r\n* We''ve had the server and its worlds since the 1.5.2 update.\r\n\r\n* When the plugin works correctly with updates, we have the NPC plugin called Citizens, and NPCs are at shops. They can also be conversed with.\r\n\r\n* The Spawn Town is protected against everything.\r\n\r\n* Although most structures were built, about 5% of them are schematics that have been found and implemented.\r\n\r\n* Some buildings were saved as schematics before/after game updates, then re-pasted after the fact to conserve them.\r\n\r\n--\r\nThis article will be updated as needed. Have fun out there! :)', 2501, 1, '2014-04-26 16:24:36', 50, 'no', ':1:2:3:55', 'About the server and its spawn point.', '2014-04-26 16:24:36', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 27, '', '', 'no', 'minecraft, article, about, dreamcraft, dreamspand, server, survival, creative', 'Finished.', ''),
(2502, 'Update: DreamCraft 2.0', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]Hey guys! Just thought I''d let everyone know that we''ve been working hard on the regular (1.7.9) Minecraft server. We''re renovating the Spawn Point, and doing other things to the server too. You''ll be happy to know that the Portals in the back of Spawn are fully functional now, and we plan to add more, as the Portal section has an upstairs now. New things are constantly being added. Come say hi to us some time! If you''re not white-listed, feel free to ask us! :)[br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 2502, 3, '2014-04-29 19:18:59', 28, 'no', ':1:2', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 13, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2503, 'Update: Multifood Mod', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]A new mod has been added to the server, developed by yours truly. It''s called Multifood (due to my lack of creativity and laziness when it comes to names), and it adds (as its name suggests) multiple foods to the game, which includes cherries, oranges, grapefruits, lemons, limes, a special fruit called limons (lemons mixed with limes), bananas, strawberries and grapes. Most grow on trees, but some grow as crops, which can be planted on tilled land. It also adds eight new colors of wooden planks to the game. This is only the Alpha version (please pardon the pun). In the future, more things will be implemented, as well as more food. It won''t be just fruit; it will be vegetables, fruit, nuts, herbs and spices. One type of juice has already been added to the game called Lemon Aid, because (when drank), it will add [i]strong[/i] regeneration for 15 seconds (I couldn''t get it to go longer, sadly; that particular potion effect has a max time limit). I will be adding more different types of juices and such in the next version. :)\n\n** The [url=http://www.dreamspand.com/mods/AlphaPack.zip]AlphaPack.zip[/url] archive has been updated with all of the current mods from the server. You should also delete OpenPeripheral from your mods list if you intend on adding the MF (MultiFood) mod, as they have ID conflicts otherwise, thanks. :)[br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 2503, 3, '2014-05-01 20:07:03', 28, 'no', ':1:2', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 15, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
(2504, 'Update: Tekkit Updates', 'Automatic update was made by: [user=1][br][br]Hey guys. Per user and OP request, we have made some mod changes:\r\n\r\n[b]Removed[/b]\r\nMFFS\r\nQCraft\r\nLogisticsPipes\r\n\r\nSo if you don''t want to mess around with those in single player, you can delete them from your mods list, if you know how. If not, contact one of us and we''ll help you. Also, removing them will substantially improve loading time and reduce a good amount of in-game lag. It''s not a requirement to remove them, but definitely a recommendation.\r\n\r\n[b]Added[/b]\r\n[url=http://www.dreamspand.com/mods/AlphaItems1.4.zip]Alpha''s Extras 1.4[/url]\r\n\r\nClick on the mods to download them. For assistance, talk to any staff member or OP. These days, adding and/or removing mods could not be easier. It''s really easy once you learn how, and this will probably be one of the last mod updates. I could be wrong about that though, it all depends on who asks to add what. We''ll check with the users first, though, to see what they think. The Tekkit server has grown substantially well, and we''re looking to expand it further, not shrink it more! So feel free to tell your friends and we''ll try to make things work. There may be maintenance on the server this week, but we''ll try our best to do it when either not a lot of people are on, or more than likely, no one at all. But don''t let it hinder your game-play! We have two other servers as well, although one is very glitchy (a hand-modded server with a manual modpack, called the Alpha Pack server, more of a ''testing'' area than anything else for mods / plugins).\r\n\r\nI''ve also removed all bans from the regular server, I think enough time has passed and things have calmed down enough. Well, I''ve cleared it except for one user, but nobody I''ve talked to in the past few months knows him but me. Someone I''ve had problems with for years, on sites and servers. He''s been very destructive and ill-mannered, arguing with users constantly and consistently breaking things built by other players with this pathetic little posse. But that''s it, everyone else is off. I figured I''d let everyone know.\r\n\r\nAlso! For those of you that are new, check the site regularly for updates. And I guess it''s time to release some news, seeing as how I''ve made some progress on this. In the not-too-distant future, your MC inventories will be synced with the web site. You will be able to buy things in-game with your tokens from here. You will be able to store and retrieve your inventory, and have different sets. Consider it as a sort of virtual storage for your things, especially with the mass amount of stuff on our servers. Tokens / in-game money will be the same thing, and will be connected through here, as well as the server. It''s a project I''ve been working on and thinking about for some time, and although I hit a dead-end with it the other night, I think I may have another path to go down with the Java coding I''m having to work with. \r\n\r\nAlso, yes, I update my mods, and the Alpha''s Items is (so far) the only one of my actual mods on the server, though I''ll eventually add my plugin too (that''s where the warps come from on the regular DreamCraft server, yours truly). Someone requested a turtle and wolf mod, and I''ve already got the model for the turtle made, the best I can with square designs...lol. It looks like the things from Spyro, it''s hilarious. But I think it looks okay. But I''ll only update my mods maybe once a month or so, unless I get asked to update them earlier. Also, if you have any ideas for mods (or a specific request in general), please feel free to ask. I really don''t mind, as long as I can do it, and if I can''t, I''ll tell you straight up. But that''s everything that''s going on right now. Have a good day everyone.\r\n\r\nThanks. :)[br][hr]This post was automatically made when the update was posted. You may view it on the updates page, or reply to it here.', 2504, 3, '2014-05-06 19:29:08', 28, 'no', ':1:2', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 15, '', '', 'no', '', '', ''),
